title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Stir shortening until creamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Mix well. Add eggs, beating until light.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cornmeal.
Add to first mixture alternately with milk.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake 25 minutes in 400° oven.
(Mixer can be used on slow speed.)

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in one pan and in another pan brown ground beef and onion.
Add tomato sauce and simmer.
Add rice when done.
Simmer until most of water is gone.
Stir in cheese.
Place mixture in long cake pan or Pyrex dish.
Bake in 400° oven until cheese melts.

title: apple crisp pudding
directions: Blend together the shortening, brown sugar, cinnamon, oatmeal and flour.
Place apples in a buttered dish.
Cover with crumb mixture.
Bake until brown.
Do not cover.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg slightly with a fork.
Stir in milk and salad oil or shortening.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Mix together, stirring just until flour is blended.
Do not overmix.
Fold in 1 cup fresh or frozen blueberries.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Enjoy and good luck!!

title: zebra pie
directions: Whip the cream; add sugar.
Spread 1 cup of Oreos in a medium size casserole dish.
Slice 1 banana over crumbs.
Top with half of whipped cream.
Make another layer just like the first.
Cover and chill for 2 hours or more.
Garnish with cherry.

title: shrimp aspic salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients. When partially set, add shrimp, olives (drained), celery and hot sauce.
Pour in mold or 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Chill until set. Serves 10 to 12.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve cold with cake or as a fruit cup.

title: tomato soup dressing(dieter's choice)
directions: Combine ingredients in jar; cover and shake thoroughly.
Use on vegetable or tossed salads.

title: coconut chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix dry ingredients together; set aside. Mix sweetened condensed milk and mustard together.
Dip chicken in milk mixture, then coat in coconut mixture.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 12-inch pan at 375°.
Drizzle with 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamy lemon meringue
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in Eagle Brand, ReaLemon and food coloring.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
In small bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until soft peaks form; gradually add sugar, beating until stiff, but not dry.
Spread meringue on top of pie, sealing carefully to edge of shell.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.
Cool. Chill before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: quickie pork chop dinner
directions: Brown chops, salt and pepper.
Place rice in baking dish. Pour orange juice over rice.
Arrange browned chops on rice.
Pour soup over everything.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: english muffin loaf
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquid
to 120° for milk and water.
Add to dry mixture and mix well.
Stir in enough flour to make stiff batter.
Sprinkle top with corn meal.
Put in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch greased pan.
Cover with wax paper for 45 minutes in a warm place.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: jamaican brown chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil (do not flour chicken). Add all ingredients and simmer, stirring occasionally. Serve with rice.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Serve with fresh vegetables.
I like carrots and cauliflower.

title: cabbage-sausage-beef goulash
directions: In a large kettle, brown sausage, beef and onion.
Drain well. Add remaining ingredients except cabbage, and mix well.
Stir in cabbage and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until cabbage is tender. Serve with French bread and a pot of pinto beans

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares and garnish with pecans, if desired.

title: festive chicken spread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and beat until smooth.
Stir in chicken, eggs and diced green onions and peppers.
Line a mold or small bowl with plastic wrap.
Fill bowl with mixture and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Invert bowl on top of leafy lettuce.
Remove plastic wrap.
Arrange green pepper strips, sesame seed, olives and red pepper on top of the spread.

Put the toasted sesame seed in a stripe down the middle of the spread. Place the green pepper strips along each side of the seed. Put olives on one side of the pepper strips and the red pepper on the opposite side.
Serve with crackers.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat
eggs
thoroughly; add sugar, syrup and salt.
Add butter and
vanilla;
beat
well.
Put pecans in bottom of pie shell. Pour
mixture
over nuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: beer pork chops
directions: Brown chops; drain on paper towel.
Cut off excess fat. Spread half of soup on bottom of baking dish.
Place chops flat in dish.
Cover with rest of soup and beer.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Use sauce for rice or potatoes.

title: strawberry peach cooler
directions: Combine strawberries and peaches in small bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar; stir gently.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes.

title: party chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Wrap each boneless chicken breast with bacon and follow by chipped beef.
Place wrapped chicken breast in a greased pan.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grilled mahimahi
directions: Melt butter and add remaining ingredients, except the fish and lemon wedges. After stirring well, add the fish and marinate for 30 minutes.
Broil for 5 to 6 minutes on each side or until the fish flakes easily with a fork.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: spinach parmesan
directions: Clean and cook spinach until tender.
Drain well.
Chop coarsely and mix in cheese, onion, cream and 4 tablespoons margarine.
Place in shallow, 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs and remaining margarine.
Heat in oven at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: the cake that won't last
directions: Mix eggs, flour, sugar, salt, soda and oil; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until well blended.
Do not beat.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Melt marshmallows on stove and mix in cranberry sauce.
Set aside.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water and add to marshmallow and cranberry sauce.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Mix and chill.

title: cranberry banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Process bananas in food processor until smooth. Add rest of ingredients and process only until evenly mixed.
Turn into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake 1 hour. Yield: 1 loaf.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring to boil.
Add cooked beets; bring to boil again and can. Makes about 8 pints.

title: perked hot spiced tea
directions: Mix tea, orange juice, lemon juice and sugar together until sugar is dissolved.
Then put in bottom of a percolator pot.
In the percolator basket, add whole cloves and cinnamon (broken). Let perk for about 10 minutes or until coffee pot shuts off. Serves 8 cups.

title: date nut bars
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar.
Beat again.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Blend into egg mixture slowly.
Add pecans, dates and vanilla and last beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
When cold, cut in 1 x 2-inch bars.
Put in bag with powdered sugar and shake to coat bars.

title: german style potato salad
directions: Fry bacon pieces.
Drain on paper towel.
Remove all but 1/4 cup bacon grease from skillet.
To grease, add onion, vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Cook over low heat, uncovered, until mixture simmers.
Pour over potato slices in bowl and toss gently to combine.
Season to taste with salt.
Garnish with bacon.

title: m j's hot sauce
directions: Mix well.
This sauce becomes better and thicker if it sets up overnight.
However, it is addictive.
If you take one bite, the whole bowl will be gone.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss together the broccoli, red onion, raisins, sunflower seeds and bacon.
Mix together the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar; stir well and pour over the broccoli salad. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: simple coconut pie
directions: Cook over medium heat until boiling.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Cool before serving.
Makes 1 pie.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour 1/2 of batter into well greased iron skillet.
Put 1/2 of cheese on the batter. Pour remaining batter into pan and add remaining cheese on top. Bake in 350° preheated oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and shape into balls.
Bake until done and drain.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix the jello with water, add all but the sour cream.
Put 1/2 in pan and let sit in refrigerator.
Then spread sour cream on top and then put the rest of jello mixture on top and refrigerate.

title: hearty hodgepodge
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook beef, onion and garlic until the beef is brown and the onion is tender.
Stir in the minestrone soup, pork and beans, water, celery, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Stir first five ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into lightly greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 minutes in a 450° oven.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and corn together; pour into greased casserole dish. Mix celery soup, sour cream and onions.
Pour on top of beans and corn.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine and Cheddar cheese.
Put on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: blueberries in snow
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O
with	boiling water.	Add pie filling and pineapple.	Put into glass baking dish.
Chill until firm.

title: bacon ball
directions: Stir dressing mix into cream cheese; roll into ball.
Roll cheese ball in the bacon bits.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 24 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: *Mixture of two cheeses is the best (white and yellow).

title: darrell's brisket
directions: Place brisket in large baking dish.
Pour honey over brisket. Sprinkle brown sugar over brisket.
Add pepper and garlic powder. Let brisket marinate overnight.

title: golden lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then flour.
In 12-inch skillet brown chicken in butter.
Add soup mix blended with water; place lemon on chicken.
Bring to boil; simmer covered 10 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Mix together soups, tomatoes and milk.
In large casserole, layer 1/3 chips, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 soup mixture, 1/2 cheese, 1/3 chips, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 soup mixture, 1/2 cheese and 1/3 chips. Bake at 350° until bubbly hot!

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate bars, water and salt in double boiler or microwave oven.
Let cool.
Fold the whipped cream into it.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Cool in refrigerator.
Can garnish with whipped cream.

title: rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix milk, rice, sugar and salt and put in a 6-cup buttered casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 2 hours.
Stir every 30 minutes.
At end, add raisins (soaked in water and drained).
Add vanilla.
Mix and bake 30 minutes more.

title: pinto casserole
directions: Fry onion with hamburger.
Mix pintos, tomato sauce, tomatoes with juice, salt and pepper.
Mix all together.
Top with 1 box of Jiffy corn muffin mix.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Delicious!

title: tropical punch
directions: In a punch bowl, combine fruit punch, lemonade and orange juice concentrates, pineapple juice, water and sugar; stir to dissolve sugar.
When ready to serve, add ice to the punch.
Pour in ginger ale; garnish with orange slices.
Gently stir.
Makes 30 (5-ounce) servings.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Empty box of potatoes and cheese mix in casserole.
Pour boiling tomatoes, water and oregano over potatoes.
Mix some pepperoni and a little cheese in.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Put rest of cheese and pepperoni on top, bake in oven until cheese melts.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let set 5 minutes.
Stir in buttermilk; set aside.
In large bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender; blend until mixture resembles corn meal.
Stir in yeast and milk mixture.
Mix well.
Place on a floured kneading board.
Knead 3 or 4 minutes.
Roll into 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on cookie sheets.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 450°.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken crescent casserole
directions: Mix chicken, celery, onion, cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise and sliced water chestnuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch glass casserole. Cook in microwave oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until good and hot. Remove from microwave oven.
Spread crescent rolls over top. Sprinkle cheese and sliced almonds over all. Bake in a 375° oven for 17 to 20 minutes or until rolls are golden brown.

title: steak saute marengo
directions: Heat 4 tablespoons butter and the oil in a saute pan.
Cut steak into cubes and the onions and carrot into quarters and saute for 5 minutes.
Season with salt and freshly ground pepper. Sprinkle with flour and blend.
Allow to color slightly; add garlic and stir.
Add wine and reduce by 2/3.
Add tomato sauce to the pan.
Put in bouquet garni (1/2 teaspoon of each:
thyme, rosemary, marjoram, basil, peppercorns and 2 bay leaves tied in cheesecloth). Add enough beef broth to cover the meat.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer very gently for 1 hour.
Scald the little onions; drain. Dry with a cloth and cook in 1 tablespoon butter until golden.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Heat water to boiling in a covered pan.
Put in the chicken, onion, celery and salt.
Cover and cook until chicken is done. Remove chicken; bone and cut meat in cubes.
Heat together soup, tomatoes and strained broth.
In a large casserole dish, place a layer of tortilla strips, chicken, then chicken soup stock with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat layering until all ingredients are used.
Cheese should be top layer.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes, then lower to 200° for about 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: velveeta cheese chocolate candy(fudge)
directions: Cube
cheese
and
melt
in double boiler or microwave. Melt margarine.	Mix all ingredients well and press into 2 (9 x 13-inch)
baking
pans.
Let
set in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: linguine with fresh tomato sauce and porcini mushrooms
directions: Pour chicken broth over dried mushrooms and
let soak at least 1 hour.
Chop the tomatoes coarsely in food processor or by hand. Saute onion in butter; add tomatoes, parsley, basil, wine and pepper.
Cook on medium-high heat until liquid is reduced by half (about 30 minutes).
Remove the mushrooms from the broth, reserving the broth.
Chop mushrooms, discarding any hard pieces. Add the mushrooms and broth and simmer again until sauce is thick. Meanwhile, cook the linguine according to package directions. Serve sauce over linguine.

title: sausage scrapple
directions: In small container blend cornmeal with 1 cup of chicken broth. Brown sausage until crumbly.
Drain fat from sausage.
Add remaining broth to sausage and bring to a boil.
Slowly stir in cornmeal mixture, stirring constantly for about 10 to 15 minutes. Add seasonings and reduce heat. Keep on stirring!
Spoon into a 4 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Cover and chill overnight or at least 3 hours. Slice into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Coat with flour and brown in butter.
Serves 4.

title: blitz torte
directions: Grease two (9-inch) cake pans, line with wax paper and grease the paper.
Beat egg whites, adding 1 cup of sugar a little at a time until egg whites are stiff.
Set aside.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix
flour,
baking
powder and cinnamon together.
Set aside. Mix
eggs	and
oil
together.
Add sugar and vanilla. Gradually stir
in flour mixture, beating well.
Add zucchini and pecans. Stir
well	and
pour
into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until lightly browned.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Blend flour mixture.
Blend egg and sugar.
Combine with orange juice and oil.
Add cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a loaf pan.

title: salmon ball
directions: Cream cheese should be at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese, lemon juice, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce well; mix in cleaned, deboned salmon, celery and onion.
Chill 3 hours after forming into ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Split chilies and remove seeds.
Put a layer of chilies in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Cover with Cheddar, add another layer of chilies and cheese.
Combine milk, eggs, cornmeal, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over chilies and cheese.
Put in oven and bake until mixture has set, about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and add Jack cheese.
Top with tomatoes and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: dark chocolate frosting
directions: Microwave butter until melted.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir and microwave, stirring everything 30 to 40 seconds, until frosting is smooth and dark chocolate color.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: bill's blueberry waffles
directions: Combine flour, eggs, milk and oil together; mix well.
Cook on waffle iron.
When waffles are done, place 1 waffle on plate.
Add heaping tablespoon of blackberries and 1 heaping teaspoon of Cool Whip and butter.
You can add as many layers to your plate as you like.

title: raisin rice pudding
directions: In a double boiler mix	rice
with
cups milk.
Cook over hot water until
tender.
Add raisins and butter. Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla, salt
and
remaining milk. Stir into hot rice mixture.
Pour into
a
greased
1 1/2 quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon or
nutmeg.
Set
pan
in hot water and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer frozen hash brown potatoes.
Mix sour cream, onion, cream of mushroom soup, salt and 1 stick melted oleo and pour over hash browns.
Next, mix grated cheese, corn flakes and 1 stick of melted oleo and place on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: christmas pretzel salad(serves 20)
directions: Mix pretzel crumbs, butter and sugar.
Pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Cool and set aside.

title: mock gefilte fish
directions: Wash fish and drain.
In 2 cups of water, add 1 sliced onion, 1 sliced carrot, seasoning and 1/4 teaspoon sugar.
Boil.
Lower heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: tomato hush puppies
directions: Mix and drop by spoonfuls into hot fat.
Drain on paper towels.
Good with seafood.

title: easy chicken very tasty
directions: Dust
chicken
breasts with flour, salt and pepper.
In nonstick frying pan, place oil and heat to medium temperature. Add chicken
and
cook about 5 minutes or until brown on both sides, turning
chicken as you cook it.
Push chicken to side of pan. Add onion and mushrooms.
Stir and cook until onion is clear, about
5 minutes.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Combine corn, beans, onion, soup and cheese in a casserole dish and bake at 375° until bubbly.
Put Ritz crackers and butter on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and put in bottom of greased casserole (2 1/2-quart).
Mix other ingredients (except crackers).
Pour over broccoli.
Put crushed crackers on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Cook slowly until vegetables are soft, 6 to 8 hours in a crock-pot turned on high.
Makes 12 to 24 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Put in bowl. Pour in pan, put it in oven 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 50°.
Take it out and cut into circles.
Wait till cool - 5 minutes.
Eat them.

title: 5 in 1 fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple; mix all ingredients.
Best if fixed and left in fridge overnight before using.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Chop onion, celery and green pepper.
Mince clove of garlic. In a 1-quart casserole dish combine onion, celery, green pepper, butter and garlic.
Cover and microwave 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Microwave, uncovered, 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir after 1 1/2 minutes.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter 5 1/2-cup souffle dish or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Beat baking mix, milk, eggs and salt with a hand beater until smooth.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Pour in souffle dish and bake until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jezebel
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator up to one year.
To serve, pour over soft cream cheese. Serve with specialty crackers.
Good with cocktails.
Also good as a glaze for ham or a dip for ham cubes.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Combine ingredients; then mix with stiffly beaten egg white. Bake slowly for 50 minutes in well-buttered pan.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread pecans and coconut on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix by directions on box and pour into pan.
Melt together cream cheese and margarine; add sugar and mix well.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until good and brown.

title: roast for two
directions: Place peeled potatoes, carrots and celery at bottom of crock-pot.
Add roast with two cups of water and 1 teaspoon of coffee.
Salt and pepper, then cover and cook for 10 hours.

title: cheesy garlic grits(great as brunch side dish or with fried chicken or ham dinner)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Prepare grits according to package directions.
Add small amount of grits to beaten egg.
Return grits mixture to pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat an additional minute or until cheese is melted.
Pour into prepared casserole; bake 30 to 40 minutes or until top is set and lightly puffed.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: x-tra special spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, blend vegie soup mix, sour cream, mayo and lemon juice.
Stir in spinach and water chestnuts.
Chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put sugar over ground cranberries and let stand 2 hours or overnight.
Add the rest of the ingredients and let stand 2 to 3 hours or overnight.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the cabbage.
Add mix to the shredded cabbage.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar.
Add
of the eggs and mix well. Then add 1/2 of the flour and mix again.
Next, add the remainder of the eggs and flour; mix well.
Pour grease into a tube pan and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: beef biscuit roll-ups
directions: Saute onion, pepper and parsley in butter until tender.
Add and brown ground beef.
Season with salt and pepper; sprinkle flour over meat and stir well.
Add bouillon cubes dissolved in 2 tablespoons hot water.
Add the rest of the water.
Cook until thick.
Cool and spread on biscuit dough rolled about 1/4-inch thick and 6 inches wide.
Roll up dough and meat mixture as a jelly roll.
Slice and bake on cookie sheet in 400° oven about 20 minutes.
Any extra roll-ups can be stored in the freezer.
Serve with cheese sauce or gravy.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1 1/3 tablespoons butter.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour remaining 1/3 cup butter into an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Toss cooked spaghetti in butter.
Cover spaghetti with 1/2 tomato sauce, Swiss cheese, 1/2 pepperoni, 1/2 Mozzarella and all of mushrooms and onion.
Sprinkle with oregano and basil. Top with remainder of tomato sauce, cheese and pepperoni.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix
soups
and
water; add rice.
Put into 9 x 12-inch pan. Sprinkle
with
curry
powder.
Lay
pieces
of
frying chicken into soup and rice mixture.
(I like thighs with skin removed or 1/2 breast pieces.) Sprinkle with 1 envelope Lipton onion soup mix.
Cover
pan tightly with foil and do not lift during baking. Bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into a pre-baked pie shell.
Top with marshmallows if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until the mixture sets.

title: crisp cucumber and onion slices
directions: Do not peel cucumbers. Score with tines of fork before slicing. Slice and separate onions into rings and combine with cucumbers.
Mix remaining ingredients and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil. While hot, pour over cucumbers. Cover. When cool, refrigerate.

title: walk around the kitchen spaghetti or everything but the kitchen
directions: Brown beef until no trace of red remains; drain off all fat and place cooked ground beef into large Dutch oven.
Add pork to same pan, browning it until thoroughly done.
Again, drain all fat.
Add cooked pork to ground beef.
Add bulk sausage to same pan; brown thoroughly, breaking up any large pieces.
Use slotted spoon to remove cooked sausage to the cooked meat in the Dutch oven.
Add minced onions to the sausage drippings, sauteing until transparent.
Add garlic; continue sauteing, but be careful not to let the garlic burn.
Use slotted spoon to remove to Dutch oven. Add celery; saute until just wilted.
Add peppers; cook at least 5 to 10 minutes.
Dump entire pan into Dutch oven, being sure to include the drippings.

title: cheddar cheese broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 11-inch pan. Mix all other ingredients, except cheese. Pour batter over melted butter and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place a layer of potatoes in a buttered baking dish.
Add minced onion.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and flour and dot with butter.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Pour hot milk over potatoes and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: turkey corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in oil till tender.
Blend in flour, gradually. Stir in turkey stock.
Blend well.
Add tomatoes, potatoes, green pepper, bay leaves, paprika, salt, thyme and cayenne.
Stir to combine.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add turkey and corn and let simmer 45 minutes more.
Makes 10, 1 cup, servings.

title: peanut butter banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; sift together.
Cream together the peanut butter and shortening in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well, then add dry ingredients alternately with banana pulp and buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly, but do not beat.
Pour batter into a well-greased loaf pan and bake for 1 hour or until done.
Cool before slicing.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain pineapple, keep juice.
Combine boiling water and Jell-O until dissolved.
Add cold water, bananas, marshmallows and pineapple.
Mix well and chill until set.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Combine liquid, sugar, flour, butter and eggs; cook until thick.
Add cream cheese and continue stirring until cheese is melted; let cool and spread over Jell-O mix.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill for 30 minutes.
Roll into finger cookies and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 325°. Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: plantation punch
directions: Stir frozen juices and lemonade into cool tea.
Pour over a block of ice in punch bowl.
Just before serving, add ginger ale. Garnish with thin slices of orange and lemon.
Makes 30 punch cup servings.

title: chocolate dream cookies
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in saucepan and stir constantly.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: spicy southwest tuna casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine soup and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients except chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Stir.
Top with chips.
Bake 5 minutes more.
tags: shredded Monterey Jack cheese with peppers

title: sausage casserole
directions: In 10-inch skillet, mix sausage, potatoes, pepper and thyme. Cook over medium heat, stirring until potatoes are browned. Reduce heat to medium; uncover and cook until potatoes are tender. Stir in all ingredients and continue cooking uncovered until vegetables are crispy and potatoes are tender.

title: glazed sausages
directions: Combine all ingredients except sausage to make glaze.
Cook until bubbly, stirring frequently.
Add sausages.
Reduce heat and cook approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Pour off excess sauce when ready to serve.
Serves 18.

title: bacon wrapped sirloin roast
directions: Cut a few slits on top of roast, for bacon drippings to penetrate meat.
Spread mustard evenly over top and sides of roast; sprinkle with thyme.
Place roast on rack in a baking pan. Cover tightly with bacon slices, wrapping around meat.
Bake at 325° until meat thermometer, if used, registers 160°.
Cooking time is about 1 3/4 hours.
Check for doneness with a fork. Juices should run slightly pink for medium rare.
Add onions 40 minutes before roast is done.

title: puto
directions: Thoroughly blend all ingredients; stir until smooth. Fill muffin pans 2/3 full with mixture.
Steam for 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center of the puto comes out clean. Serve with grated coconut.

title: best yet pear cake
directions: Mix pears, pecans and sugar; then set aside.
Beat eggs; add oil, flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Add pear mixture; mix well.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Butter 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or a 10 3/4 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan. In medium saucepan, stir sugar, milk and salt. Boil 10 minutes. Add butter. Boil until it will form a soft ball when tested in cold water. Add vanilla and peanut butter. Beat and pour into buttered pan.

title: skinny french fries
directions: Put potato strips or slices on ice to crisp.
Drain; pat dry on paper towel.
Spread on pan (spray pan with Pam).
Sprinkle with oil.
Shake pan to spread oil.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn frequently.

title: cheesecake
directions: Let cream cheese sit out at room temperature to soften.
Place cream cheese in a bowl and gradually add powdered sugar, stirring until smooth and creamy (no lumps).
After all powdered sugar is added and mixture is creamy, fold in Cool Whip and stir until well blended.
Separate into the two pie crusts and refrigerate.

title: parsley butter sauce
directions: Combine the shallots, vinegar and wine in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook until reduced by half.
Add the broth and cream and bring to a boil.
Cook at a rolling boil about 45 seconds. Swirl in the butter.
Add the salt and pepper and stir in the mustard and parsley.
Yields about 3/4 cup.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Wash and cut up eggplant into 1-inch cubes.
Sprinkle with salt and place in a colander to drain at least 1 hour, then rinse. Cut plum tomatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
Julienne green and red bell peppers, and red onion.
Crush the garlic.
Cut squash into bite sized rounds.
Place oil in a hot skillet over medium heat. Saute the eggplant until just tender, about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add onions, garlic, peppers and squash.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When veggies are tender add tomatoes, red wine vinegar and black olives.
Simmer just enough to heat tomato and olives.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: osgood pie
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside. Mix all other ingredients together and then fold in egg whites last. Pour into unbaked pie shell (unless a large 9 or 10-inch shell is used, this will make 2 pies). Bake in slow oven at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. The meringue comes to the top and the cinnamon makes it a nice brown topping for the pie.

title: swedish meatballs i
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Shape into balls the size of a walnut. Brown in 1/4 cup hot fat or vegetable oil. Remove meatballs and make gravy. Return meatballs to gravy; cook 15 to 20 minutes. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chinese ribs
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar and m.s.g.
Cut ribs in two and wash. Marinate ribs in soy sauce at least 2 hours.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour on broiling rack.
Turn ribs over halfway through cooking. Serve ribs with fried rice and pineapple chunks for a little something different.

title: caramels
directions: Generously butter 2 loaf pans.
Mix first 6 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Over medium heat, boil to hard ball stage or to 250° on candy thermometer; stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts (nuts are optional).
Pour 1/2 of mixture into each loaf pan.
Cool at least 4 hours.
Remove from pans and cut into squares.
Squares may be dipped or half dipped into melted chocolate chips.

title: 6 week muffins
directions: Mix ingredients and store in refrigerator.
Use as needed. Lasts 6 weeks.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Melt butter; add onion, flour, sugar and sour cream.
Melt 3 slices Swiss cheese, cut up, and mix all with green beans which have been cooked 5 minutes and drained.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour covered on until bubbles.
Serves 6.

title: micah's favorite supper crepes
directions: Mix
together
cottage cheese and sugar with mixer; set aside.

title: beef sausage
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Form into rolls and wrap in double aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Unwrap.
Turn off oven and let dry until cool.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix and Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients and store in airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples and water in oblong baking dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: microwave rice
directions: Combine in microwave dish.
Microwave on 50% for 17 minutes.

title: rich cocoa brownies
directions: Sift flour and cocoa.
Add sugar gradually to thoroughly beaten eggs, then, add melted butter.
Add flour mixture; mix well, then add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 14 x 8-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine biscuit mix, sugar, cinnamon and allspice.
Add evaporated milk, pumpkin, oil, eggs and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Cook on grill until golden brown.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Blend milk and lemon juice with wire whisk until well mixed. Pour into crust.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream. Keep refrigerated.

title: chewy walnut squares
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan.
Stir egg, brown sugar and vanilla together.
Quickly stir in flour, mixed with salt and soda, then nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 16 (2-inch) squares.

title: apple grunt
directions: Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until the biscuits are light brown and not doughy.
Put on a plate and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Serve.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs and oil. Stir until moistened.
Do not beat.
Add vanilla, pineapple, nuts and bananas. Stir until mixed.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: diabetic fudge
directions: Combine milk and cocoa in saucepan; cook and beat over low heat until cocoa is dissolved.
Add butter, sugar replacement, salt and vanilla.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add cereal crumbs and work in with a wooden spoon.
Cool 15 minutes.
Divide in half.
Roll each half into a tube 8-inches long.
Roll each tube in chopped nuts.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill overnight.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef bombay
directions: Heat a Dutch oven or large cooking pot with lid; add oil. Brown diced onion; remove onion.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Pour broth on bread and onion and celery in 1/2 stick of butter.
Put with broth and bread.
Put 3 tablespoons of flour, 1 stick of butter and 1 cup water for sauce.
Stir until comes to a boil.
Add 1 can cream of chicken soup.
Take meat off chicken and place over dressing and pour sauce over. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ribbon cookies
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Add salt and baking powder.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Divide into 3 parts.
Add cherries and food coloring to 1, melted chocolate and nuts to the second and leave the third plain. Line a bread pan with wax paper.
Pack chocolate dough on bottom, plain in the center and cherry dough on top.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Turn out of pan.
Cut into 3 strips and slice thin.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: christmas braid
directions: Thaw frozen dough; roll to 12-inch square.
Cut in 3 strips. Spread butter or margarine down lengthwise center of each strip. Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over butter.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bring dough up around filling, sealing edges to form 3 ropes.
Place on greased baking sheet and loosely braid. Let rise until double (about 30 minutes).
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Combine confectioners sugar and enough milk to make a thin glaze.
Drizzle over braid while it is still warm. Sprinkle top with red sugar and trim with pecan halves.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Mix in other ingredients.
Place tomato slices in the bottom of a greased baking dish.
Place an ice cream scoop of spinach mixture on each tomato slice.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: garden fresh omelet
directions: Fry pepper and onion in a little olive oil or cooking oil on medium or low heat.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together with rotary beater.
Pour into lined 9-inch pie pan.
Bake until set, about 40 to 45 minutes, at 375°.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix vegetables, salt and pepper; drain.
Heat vinegar, sugar and oil to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Keeps up to 7 days. This is very good with barbecue.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread over bottom of pan, pie filling, pineapple and dry cake mix.
Sprinkle over top, coconut and pecans.
Pour melted oleo over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Beat together eggs, oil and sugar until light in color.
Stir in zucchini. Stir in melted chocolate; mix well.
Stir together flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Set aside 1/4 cup. Add flour mixture to egg mixture, mixing just to blend.
Toss nuts with the remaining 1/4 cup flour mixture. Add to cake mixture and stir to blend.
Spoon into greased tube pan or 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done with toothpick.

title: black walnut cake* * * * *
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine buttermilk and soda, stirring until soda is dissolved.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 22 to 25 minutes. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on rack. Spread with Cream Cheese Frosting and press walnut halves around the sides.

title: belle's broasted chicken livers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and place chicken livers in 9-inch baking dish.
Slice butter.
Place over livers.
Sprinkle with salt and black pepper.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Place in oven and cook for 40 to 45 minutes, turning and basting periodically.
Do not allow livers to cook dry.
Add water as necessary for a tasty sauce.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except cheese and put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake 2 hours at 250°.

title: pumpkin cheesecake pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and pumpkin pie spice on medium speed. Stir in pumpkin. Add eggs and mix until blended. Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.

title: pig in a blanket
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Slit wieners to within 1/2-inch of ends; insert 3 strips of cheese in each slit.
Separate dough into 8 triangles; wrap dough over wiener, keeping cheese up.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, cheese side up.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick homemade pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Add flour and meal.
Mix well, then add syrup, vanilla, melted butter and last add pecans.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: buttermilk yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in melted shortening.
Combine dry ingredients in a small bowl.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk to yeast mixture; mix well.

title: holiday wassail
directions: In a large kettle, combine tea and sugar. Add juices, cinnamon sticks and 12 of the cloves.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Serve warm or cool.
Garnish punch bowl with orange slices and the rest of the cloves.

title: caramelized banana topping
directions: In medium saucepan, over medium-high heat, bring syrup to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low and add banana slices.
Cook for 5 to 7 minutes, or until banana is golden brown and maple syrup has thickened.

title: cream cheese
directions: Mix and cook 25 minutes at 325°.

title: creamy mushroom bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter shallow baking dish.
Arrange mushrooms in dish, stem side down.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Boil butter, margarine and sugar together for 2 minutes. Break crackers apart and spread on cookie sheet in single layer. Pour sauce over crackers.
Top with sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Take off cookie sheet to cool.

title: butter nut chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs until light and foamy in large bowl.
Beat in sugar, vanilla and margarine until creamy. Combine flour to egg mixture.
Mix until blended.
Stir in nuts at low speed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Saute meat in olive oil.
Add spaghetti sauce and 1 can of water.
Cook 15 minutes on the stove.
Season to taste.
Cook lasagna with oil.
Mix cottage cheese, cheese and 4 eggs.
Put in casserole.
Layer sauce and lasagna.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: quick chili mac(working family)
directions: Brown hamburger and onion with green pepper.
Drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Then reduce and simmer 15 minutes or so.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix
all
the
ingredients
until well blended.
Enjoy! Bake in two greased loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: low-fat paella
directions: In large pot, saute chicken, onion and garlic until chicken is slightly brown.
Add water, rice, broth, seasonings and tomatoes. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in peas and pimientos.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mac and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Butter Pyrex dish.
Place a layer of Cheddar cheese, layer macaroni, layer of cheese, etc.
Finish with layer of cheese.
Add about 1/3 cup milk to complete.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until cheese is golden and bubbly.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach, drain and tear in small pieces.
Put in salad bowl, sprinkle with bacon and eggs; chill.
Mix remaining ingredients and chill.
Just before serving, pour over spinach mixture and toss.

title: chicken with olives
directions: Put the chicken in boiling water for 7 minutes.
Remove chicken, discard the water and return chicken to pan.
Add all ingredients, except the olives.
Simmer 2 hours, add the olives and simmer 15 minutes.

title: barbeque meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Spoon into a 10 x 6 x 2 inch baking dish and shape into a loaf.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup tomato sauce and remaining ingredients and pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes, basting occasionally with sauce.

title: chicken-rice casserole(microwave)
directions: Mix together rice, soup, mushrooms, water and onion soup in a 5 quart casserole dish.
Add chicken pieces.
Cook on full power for
to
minutes.
After 11 minutes turn chicken pieces over and sprinkle with paprika for color.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix and cream together butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pseudo-southwestern quinoa
directions: First of all quinoa (pronounced "keen-wa") is an alkalizing grain.
It is hardy and contains the highest amount if protein of any grain.
It cooks quickly and makes a delicious, crunchy dish. It is high in calcium, phosphorus, iron, B vitamins, and vitamin E and has an ideal balance of amino acids.
Wash quinoa thoroughly to remove the saponin, the rust-colored coating that protects this seed against insects, birds, and the sun.
While cooking, the germ on the outside of the grain unfolds like a partial spiral giving the finished cooked product a lovely appearance.

title: parmesan baked potatoes
directions: Pour butter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over butter or margarine. Place potatoes with cut side down over cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes or until tender. Makes 8 servings.

title: tex-mex chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, 1/4 cup picante sauce, cream cheese, onion and oregano in skillet.
Place over low heat until cheese is melted. Stir in 1/2 cream cheese.
Place chicken mixture in center of each tortilla.
roll and place seam side down in lightly greased 12 x 7-inch baking dish. Spoon remaining 3/4 cup picante sauce over enchiladas. Cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: vietnamese egg roll
directions: All ingredients finely chopped.
In large bowl combine ingredients together well.
Fill each egg roll skin with 2 tablespoons mixture.
Fold 2 sides over mixture, brushing last fold with water.
Roll between palms to seal and shape.
When ready to cook, preheat oil to 325°.
Drop egg rolls into hot oil. Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper toweling. Keep warm in oven until ready to serve.
Serve with Chinese hot mustard or a sweet-sour sauce.
Can be made in advance and frozen. Serves 8.

title: cheese bread
directions: Thaw the corn.
Heat the oven to 350°.
Butter a 9-inch cast-iron skillet or cake pan.
Cut cheese into slices about 1/4-inch thick.
Slice the peppers.
Combine cornmeal, baking powder and salt; stir in thawed corn.
Melt the butter.
Mix together the eggs, sour cream and melted butter.
Pour egg mixture into cornmeal mixture; stir until combined, but still lumpy.
Pour in the remaining batter.
Bake until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm from the skillet.

title: vichyssoise
directions: Use only white part of leeks and chop fine.
Saute leeks and onion in melted butter until soft (about 10 minutes).
Stir in potatoes and chicken broth.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer uncovered for 45 minutes until potatoes are done.
Remove from heat and put in blender.
Blend until pureed.
Stir in cream, milk, salt, pepper and spices.
Cool and serve!

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; mixture should be very moist but not soupy.
Pour into buttered 9-inch by 9-inch baking dish.
Place on middle rack of non-preheated oven.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour 15 minutes, until top is golden brown.
Serve warm with Amaretto Sauce.
Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: lemon and chive potatoes
directions: Pare narrow strips around center of potatoes.
Mix remaining ingredients in a 2-quart microwavable casserole dish.
Microwave on High until butter is melted, about 60 seconds.
Add potatoes, turning to coat with butter.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes; stir.
Microwave until potatoes are tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: low-fat banana muffins(.7 grams of fat each)
directions: Combine sugar, egg substitute and one banana.
Add remaining three bananas and flour along with baking soda and vanilla.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins. Enjoy!!

title: dipped peanut butter sandwich cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter on half of the crackers.
Top with remaining crackers to make sandwiches.
Refrigerate.

title: yuletide layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 inch baking pan in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted butter, stir well and press onto bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with nuts, coconut and Shapes & Morsels.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.

title: eagle brand chocolate icing
directions: Use small pan. Stir constantly until mixture thickens and becomes shiny. Pour immediately over cake. Sets fast!

title: turkette
directions: Cook
spaghetti
according
to	directions
on package. Drain and
rinse	with hot water.
Combine remaining ingredients, except the cheese.	Add to drained spaghetti and blend. Pour
into 1	1/2 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake
at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.	Allow 15 minutes more baking time if frozen.

title: bacon-wrapped green beans
directions: Drain green beans.
Cut slices of bacon in half.
(You want 2 short pieces instead of 1 long piece.)
Take about 8 green beans and lay on end of short piece of bacon.
Wrap bacon around green beans.
Place on cookie sheet.
Repeat until all green beans have been used.
Place in a 375° oven and bake about 40 minutes. Remove when bacon reaches desired crispness.
Makes about 20.

title: cranberry holiday salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple, juice and nuts.
Pour in an 8 x 8-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Layer bread slices in pan 2 layers high.
Beat eggs with milk. Add nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add vanilla.
Pour over slices of bread. Place, covered, in refrigerator overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, then add to other ingredients.
Refrigerate to blend flavors.

title: pound cake
directions: Add shortening, vanilla, egg yolks and 1/2 cup milk.
Add flour and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl. Add rest of milk.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Spoon batter into prepared pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy onion pie
directions: Prepare pastry.
Chill, but do not bake.
Toss Swiss cheese and flour in pie shell.
Cover with sauteed onion slices and sliced tomatoes.
Sprinkle with basil and oregano.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Beat eggs in small bowl; add the half and half. Pour egg mixture into the pie plate.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mock whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: salsa spread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Top spread with remaining ingredients.
Serve with assorted crackers, tortilla chips, etc. Recipe doubles easily for a large crowd.

title: crab bisque
directions: Marinate crab in sherry overnight.
Next day, mix everything together and heat thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 400°.
Thaw pie crust 10 minutes. Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake crust for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain excess fat and add seasoning mix, according to package directions.
In small bowl, combine refried beans and salsa; mix well.
Spread 1/2 of bean mixture in bottom of pie crust.
Top with 1/2 of seasoned meat, 1 cup of cheese and crushed chips.
Repeat layers, excluding chips.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with lettuce, tomato, jalapenos, olives and sour cream.
Add additional sauce to taste.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Add cooking oil. Sift flour, cinnamon, salt and soda together.
Add to batter and mix well.
Stir in apples, pecans and coconut.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour in batter and bake 1 hour at 350°.
(If dough is too dry, add a little water, but not too much.)

title: peanut butter candy balls
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into balls.
Great healthy snack.

title: whole wheat potato bread
directions: In a large bowl mix the first four ingredients.
(A cooked mashed potato should be added to the potato water.
Instant potatoes can be used but should be runny and not solid.)
Add yeast dissolved in warm water.
Stir in whole wheat flour.
Let rise in warm place until double.
Stir down and add white flour.
Finish kneading in the flour and let rise until double.
Punch down and make into loaves, cinnamon rolls or bread rolls.
Let rise and bake until done and brown.
Makes 5 big loaves.

title: broccoli and romaine lettuce
directions: Fry diced bacon until crisp.
Add broccoli; stir quickly until pieces are coated.
Add 1/4 cup water; cover and cook for 4 minutes.
Uncover; add romaine, salt and sugar and stir-fry for three minutes.

title: garden soup
directions: Salt the water and bring it to a boil.
Add the carrots, potatoes, tomatoes, scallions and lima beans and boil gently for 30 minutes.
Add the green beans, okra and corn and simmer for about 15 minutes longer.
Place a spoonful of cooked white rice in the center of each soup plate and ladle some hot soup over it.
Pass a bowl of Provincial Sauce, Pistou (recipe follows), for each diner to stir into his soup.

title: a b c noodle casserole
directions: Chop ham, cheese and onion.
Mix with cooked noodles.
Beat eggs.
Stir in milk, cream and salt.
Spoon over noodles.
Pour into greased muffin pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Bake in well-greased casserole dish at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted butter over dish.
Bake for 15 minutes more until crumbs are golden brown.

title: honey barbecue wings
directions: Mix honey, brown sugar and catsup.
Dip chicken in flour and season with garlic salt and pepper.
Fry until golden brown. Place chicken on paper towels to drain grease.
Place chicken in casserole dish and smother with honey barbecue sauce.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: holiday squares
directions: Beat butter and sugar at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each at low speed.
Add flour gradually, then juice and vanilla.
Pour batter into greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Score into 24 squares.
Put a heaping teaspoonful of pie filling on each piece.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with 10x sugar or whipped cream.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Beat together sugar, soup, shortening and vanilla.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to wet ingredients and mix well. Pour into a greased and floured cake pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and ice with vanilla or cream cheese icing.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Sift together baking powder, soda, salt and spices. Combine in separate bowl the pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs. Then add dry ingredients and softened butter. Stir in nuts. Spread in well-greased pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: robert redford cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix according to package directions. Slightly cool and punch holes in sheet cake.
Mix pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil.
Pour over sheet cake.

title: jimmie's hot meat-cheez dip
directions: Brown meat (break up real fine).
Add rest of ingredients. Serve with chips or fresh veggies.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Fill a large salad bowl half full with shredded lettuce.
Add in layers: chopped celery, green pepper, onion, and peas.
Mix together mayonnaise and sour cream and spread over layer of peas. Do not mix. Sprinkle sugar over dressing and cover top of salad with shredded cheese.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon on top of cheese layer.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 8 hours.

title: candied peanuts
directions: Mix
ingredients.
Cook and stir constantly until peanuts dry out.
Bake for about 20 minutes in 300° oven; stir every 5 minutes.
If peanuts don't seem roasted, cook longer.

title: southwest pork loin roast
directions: Roll roast in 1/2 of the chili powder. Combine the remaining chili powder with the jelly and heat on low heat in a small saucepan. Use 1/2 of this glaze to pour over the roast in pan. Cover and bake at 350° to 375° for 75 to 90 minutes. Use your judgment - temperature and time depend on your oven. Check directions on label of roast if needed. When roast is done, remove cover and spoon the remainder of the glaze over the roast. Set aside until you are ready to serve.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Lightly brown the ground beef in butter; drain.

In a large pot, add all of the ingredients except tomatoes and rice or noodles and simmer for 1 hour or until the potatoes are slightly tender. Then add the tomatoes and the rice or noodles and simmer for 30 additional minutes or until the noodles are of desired softness. Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: sauteed pork chops
directions: In a skillet or electric frypan, heat piece of fat trimmed from chop until melted.
Remove.
Brown chops slowly in fat until rich golden brown on both sides, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour off excess fat; season with salt.
Add basil and milk.
Cover and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and salt. Beat eggs and oil until light and foamy.
Add vanilla.
Gradually blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in apples and walnuts.
Pour batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan on rack.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Serves 12.

title: turkey chili with black beans
directions: If using ground turkey, brown it in a large skillet, draining off any fat.
Add onion, bell pepper and garlic and saute 5 minutes.
(If using cooked turkey, saute onion, bell pepper and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil for 5 minutes, then add turkey.)
Add all remaining ingredients except cilantro and cheese.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes, uncovered, until mixture thickens slightly.
Add cilantro, then ladle into bowls and top each serving with 1 tablespoon cheese.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and baking powder in large mixing bowl. Fold in oil and oranges with juice.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in 3 (8-inch) greased and floured pans.
Cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, milk and peanut butter until creamy. Fold in Cool Whip.
Beat lightly until mixed and put in crust. Refrigerate.

title: ambrosia spring salad mold
directions: Take mandarin orange juice and add cold water to juice to make 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl.
Stir 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid and refrigerate 1 1/4 hours until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping with wire whip until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Stir in fruit and coconut. Spoon into 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm.
Unmold on a large plate.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage together; then add cheese.
Bake ingredients at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cook until bubbly and cheese is golden brown.

title: chicken with herbs
directions: Rub chicken with garlic, then salt and pepper.
Throw away garlic.
Melt butter with oil in small saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice, parlsey and basil.
Brush chicken all over with mixture, then place skin-side down on lined broiler rack. Place under boiler for 7 to 10 minutes on each side, basting frequently with butter mixture.
After 15 minutes, test chicken for doneness by inserting skewer into thigh, if juices run clear, the bird is done.
Spoon over any remaining butter mixture.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done. Boil spaghetti in broth from chicken. (If not enough add the can of chicken broth). Debone chicken while noodles are cooking. Cut up cheese into blocks (small). Place cheese and milk in pot; melt over low heat. After cheese sauce is melted, add mushrooms, Ro-Tel and chicken together. When noodles are at your desired tenderness, add sauce with noodles and season to desired taste. Enjoy your dinner.

title: pepper relish
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in glass bowl.
Let stand overnight; then drain.
Mix other 6 ingredients in pan and bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add pepper mix and boil 3 minutes. Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: ice cream
directions: For Flavored Ice Cream:
Use eight bananas, 6 to 8 peaches or 1 quart strawberries.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Whip strawberry Jello and Cool Whip.
Add fresh strawberries. Pour in pie shell.
Top off with more Cool Whip.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix together and pour into greased dish.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mash cream cheese.
Add peppermint and coloring.
Mix sugar. Knead until like pie dough.
Roll into balls the size of marbles. Place one side in small amount of sugar.
Press sugar side into mold; ummold at once.
Get mold from cake decorating supply.

title: quick raisin bars
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, water, butter and raisins. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Let cool.
Blend in flour, cinnamon, baking soda and nutmeg.
Pour into lightly greased, 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Frost with powdered sugar icing or serve as is.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spread butter or margarine on bottom and sides of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer potatoes and onion in prepared casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Arrange ham slices over top.
Spoon soup evenly over ham slices. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until done.

title: dirt(in a flower pot, or be creative, any container will do.)
directions: Remove icing from
cookies and crush cookies in chopper or food processor
until
granular-like.
This
is
the
dirt. Cream the margarine, cream cheese and 10x sugar together.
Mix the pudding with the milk
and fold in the Cool Whip and blend with the first 3 ingredients.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water (not hot).
Add shortening and mix.
Add salt and sugar and stir well, then add your flour. Cover and put in refrigerator to raise overnight.
Bake in oven at 375° until golden brown.

title: bacon dressing
directions: Fry cut-up bacon.
Beat eggs, sugar, vinegar and water.
Add mixture to fried bacon and bring to a boil.
Pour over dandelion or lettuce.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; do not drain juices. Chill in refrigerator. Makes good for a punch.

title: vidalia onion pie(from my sister filomena)
directions: Saute
onions
in butter.
Scrape into a bowl.
Combine eggs and
sour cream; mix lightly.
Add to onions and butter. Season with
salt,
pepper
and Tabasco sauce.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle
with
cheese.
Bake
at 450° for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 20 additional minutes.
This pie is delicious.

title: king ranch pie
directions: Brown meat; add seasonings.
Sear onion and pepper.
Mix liquids together in pan and heat.
Line bottom of casserole dish with chips; put layer of meat, liquid, then cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Mix together by hand.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Freeze overnight.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Mix into the cole slaw.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Combine the apples, granulated sugar and brown sugar and let set for 1 hour.
Then drain off juice and retain.

title: gold rush brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a well-greased and floured baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: buckeyes(if you like peanut butter cups, try these!)
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: ranch dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients with electric mixer or in blender. Chill before serving.

title: dunbar macaroni pie
directions: Cook macaroni until tender and drain (set aside).
Brown hamburger with finely chopped onion.
Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: idaho oven fries
directions: Slice potatoes 1/8 in. to 1/16 in. thickness, and place in ice water.
Drain.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Pour melted butter or oil on lrg. baking sheet.
Add potato slices to pan, turning to coat.
Season with Italian seasoning or your choice of flavors. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until tender.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Place rolls flat on cookie sheet with sides touching. Bake at 375° 10 to 13 minutes until brown. Cool, mix cream cheese, mayo. & dressing mix. Spread on cooled dough. Top with vegetables such as broccoli, cauliflower, carrots & radishes. Chill before serving.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature. Cream the cream cheese.
Mix in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour in pie shell. Chill for 1 hour.
Top with cherries and serve.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spread uncooked rice in a long, greased casserole dish. Place chicken pieces over rice. Chicken may be cooked with or without skin. Mix water with soup and pour over the chicken. Add salt and pepper to taste. Cook for 1 hour at 350° or until chicken is tender. Finished dish should be brown on top. Serve while hot.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In top of double boiler, mix flour, cocoa, sugar and salt.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Place on bottom of double boiler in which water is boiling.
Cook on high heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: strawberry chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Separate eggs.
Combine the yolks, oil, water and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
With electric mixer on low, gradually beat yolk mixture into flour mixture until smooth.
With clean beaters, beat whites with cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into batter.

title: antipasto
directions: Place lettuce on large serving dish.
Artistically add all other ingredients except dressing.
Be creative.
Drizzle with Italian dressing and serve.

title: mexican wedding cakes (cookies)
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add flour, salt and extract.
Beat hard.
Roll dough into log about 25-cent piece in diameter.
Cut in 3/4-inch slices.
Bake on ungreased tray at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still hot.
Makes 2 dozen (3/4-inch) cookies.

title: excellent microwave sweet pickles
directions: In a small bowl or measuring pitcher, combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix cucumbers and onions in microwave bowl.
Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers and onions.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 5 minutes. Stir well. Return to microwave for 5 minutes more. Cool.
Pour into quart jar and refrigerate.
Pickles are ready to eat when thoroughly chilled. Store in refrigerator. Makes 1 quart.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Put in a large bowl.
Melt 1 stick margarine. Add sugar, salt and milk. Mix in flour; let rise.
Roll out and cut in strips of dough. Melt 1 stick of margarine. Dip strips of dough in melted margarine and place in layers in tube pan.
Let rise and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
To serve, just pull strips off, don't cut.

title: chicken waterzooi(well known belgian dish)
directions: Easier if cooked in the crock-pot.
Cut chicken.
Take off the skin.
Cut vegetables in small chunks.
Pour 1 can chicken broth and water (if needed) and salt and pepper.
Cook on slow in the crock-pot until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: new fangled bread pudding
directions: You will need a 17-inch Pyrex dish (lightly buttered).

title: grandma jacobs' pudding dessert
directions: Combine puddings and water.
Cook over medium heat to boiling point.
Remove from burner; add jello.
Put whole mixture in refrigerator to cool.
Mix in oranges and Cool Whip; cool for 2 hours.
(Any kind of jello flavors and matching fruit can be used.)

title: broiled fish
directions: Combine all ingredients except fish.
Add fish and marinate 3 hours or more.
Turn occasionally.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
(210 calories)

title: old time beef stew
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil.
Add 2 cups water and next 9 ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bay and garlic.
Add vegetables, cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Thicken liquid with flour, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: date nut bread
directions: Add soda to dates and pour hot coffee over them.
Let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Mix flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add butter and walnuts, mix thoroughly.
Stir into date mixture.
Add egg well beaten and vanilla.
Let rise 15 minutes in pan and bake 1 hour in 350 degree oven.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Press into a baking dish. Store in refrigerator to retain flavor.
Make 48 hours before serving.

title: easy cheese balls
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature.
Chop beef and onions into small bits.
Mix all ingredients together.
Make into 3 or 4 balls and wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat with electric mixer. Add bread and pineapple with juice.
Put into a buttered casserole.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Chop or grate cabbage in large bowl.
Mix all together the carrot, cabbage, onion, celery and green pepper.

title: rotisserie chicken
directions: Prepare chicken by loosening the breast skin from the meat. Place 3/4 teaspoon rosemary and 1 tablespoon of butter on each side of the breast under the skin.
Take the remaining 1/2 teaspoon of rosemary and place inside the cavity.
Truss the bird. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to your taste.
Rotisserie for 2 hours, or until meat pulls from the bones easily.

title: chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Press into ungreased 12-inch pizza pan. Spread center area very thin. Bake at 350° until well browned.
Cool before cutting into pie shaped wedges.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Layer beans, sour cream mixture, tomatoes, etc.
Serve with chips.

title: unbaked caramel cookies
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and evaporated milk to a boil.
Remove from heat and add pudding mix and oatmeal.
Cool 15 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper lined tray.

title: janney's stew
directions: Boil chicken til done. Let cool. Chop chicken up. Brown ground beef. Drain. In a big stew pot, mix all ingredients thoroughly. Cook on medium-low for 45 minutes or until hot.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly, drain. Add garlic and onion.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add ketchup, oregano, sugar, cream cheese, tomato sauce and cheese.
heat to serving temperature.
Spoon into dish.
Serve hot with chips.

title: red clam sauce
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Saute garlic and pepper. Add Parmesan cheese, oregano and parsley.
Mix completely.
Add oil, clams and sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over linguini.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend with marshmallow cream.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add cheese to melt. Add soup.
Cook about one minute.
Cook broccoli according to package instructions.
Drain broccoli and place in casserole dish. Pour cheese and soup mixture over broccoli.
Cut 4 to 6 slices of bread into croutons.
Drizzle with remaining margarine.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut or pineapple pie
directions: Separate eggs; beat egg yolks well and add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour, milk and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Add coconut or pineapple.
Save about 1/4 cup of pineapple to put on top of meringue.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue; add coconut or pineapple on top of meringue.
Bake at 300° for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: garden stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Pierce potatoes and microwave on High for 12 minutes.
Bake in oven for 15 minutes.
Slice off potato tops.
Scoop out pulp, keeping skins intact.
Mash pulp in medium bowl.
In a small skillet on medium heat, saut onions in butter about 5 minutes.
Add broccoli, salad dressing and onion to potato pulp and mix well.
Add 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and mix.
Brush outside of potato skin shells with oil.
Spoon potato mixture into shells, dividing evenly.
Place on baking sheet and sprinkle with the rest of Cheddar cheese.
Bake potatoes until heated through about 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley, salt and pepper to taste.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, salt and lemon juice; beat well. Sift flour, soda and spices. Add flour mixture to sugar mixture and beat. Add fruit and nuts; mix well. Bake in a 10-inch stem pan which has been greased and floured. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. A Bundt pan is ideal. This cake freezes well.

title: thyme, onion and chives muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flours, baking powder, salt, thyme, onion, and chives.
In a separate bowl mix the butter, egg and milk.
Add the liquid ingredients to the dry, stirring only until the dry ingredients are moist.
DO NOT OVER MIX!
Spoon the batter into well oiled or paper lined muffin cups.
Bake for about 20 minutes at 375 degrees or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes clean.

title: tomato and olive penne
directions: Cook pasta according to package instructions until al dente, about 13 minutes. Drain.

title: peanut butter rolls
directions: Pour sugar in bowl.
Melt butter and pour into sugar.
Blend well by stirring.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture onto surface that has been dusted with dry confectioners sugar.
Knead about
1 minute.
Flatten dough out.
Put peanut butter on dough.
Spread out.
Roll up into one large roll.
Cut into slices and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix Marshmallow Creme, sugar, evaporated milk, butter and salt.
Bring to a boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chips and nuts.
Pour in Pyrex dish and cool.

title: best beans ever
directions: Fry beef and onions; set aside.
Mix ketchup, mustard, vinegar and salt.
Combine with beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no meat gravy
directions: Melt and brown butter in a saucepan; add hot water.
When cooking, stir in dissolved flour.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring all the time.
Add salt.
Tastes like real gravy.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well, but only use half of the shredded cheese.
Put in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle the rest of the shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup water and set aside.
Bring to boil 2 cups water, sugar and lemon extract.
Stir in dissolved cornstarch.
Remove from heat and stir in pinch of salt and dissolved gelatin.
Add red coloring to make a strawberry shade. Set aside to cool, stirring often until really cold.
Have whole, ripe berries washed and dry as possible.
Add filling to berries and, using a fork and a light touch, mix thoroughly.
Do not bruise or mash berries.
Pile in baked pie shell and chill in refrigerator.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: easy baked chicken and potato dinner
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Place 1 chicken breast half in each corner of the pan.
Cut unpeeled potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Place potatoes, onions and pepper into center of pan.
Pour melted margarine over chicken and vegetables.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese, garlic powder and paprika.
Bake for 40 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear, stirring vegetables once halfway through the cooking.
Makes 4 servings.
Add carrots, broccoli or other vegetables for variety.

title: orange french dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Chill before serving. Yield: 1 1/2 cups.
Good on fruit!

title: pluckin' cake
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths and roll into little balls.
Put brown sugar, granulated sugar and cinnamon into a bowl and mix well. Put each biscuit ball into mixture and coat well. Place biscuits into a Bundt pan and press down lightly.
Melt the oleo and pour it over the biscuits. Add milk and sprinkle remaining sugar mixture over the biscuits. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cake is a light brown. You may want to
add a little more cinnamon or brown sugar to the top of the cake when you remove it from the oven.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Put the brown sugar, margarine and cornstarch together in a saucepan.
Cook until smooth.

title: pizzelle cookies
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Add cooled margarine and vanilla or anise.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add to egg mixture.
Dough will be sticky enough to be dropped by spoon.
Drop by spoonful into Pizzelle iron.

title: danish puff
directions: Measure first cup of flour into a bowl.
Cut in butter. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of water.
Mix with a fork.
Round into a ball.
Divide in half.
Pat into two strips, 12 x 13-inch. Place 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.

title: spaghetti ala carbonara alfredo
directions: Cook bacon and onion until bacon is crisp and onion golden. Add wine.
Cook over low heat until wine evaporates.
Add cream and heat gently.
Do not boil.
In a large pasta dish, beat eggs, cheese, pepper, parsley and nutmeg.
Mix in spaghetti and coat well as quickly as possible.
Pour in bacon mixture.
Stir quickly.
Add salt to taste.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 people.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef and bacon.
Add onions.
Add other seasonings. Drain lima and kidney beans.
Add beans to meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: company mashed potatoes
