directions: Combine all ingredients except salt in greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot asparagus rolls(or hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Trim crusts, flatten bread with rolling pin.
Blend cheese and egg.
Spread on bread, roll asparagus spear in each slice (2 if asparagus is small), fasten with toothpicks.
Dip in melted margarine.
Bake 15 minutes, or until brown in 400° oven.
They freeze nicely and if frozen remove from freezer and let thaw in refrigerator, then bake.

title: butter horns
directions: Make 10 balls.
Put in fridge for 2 hrs.
Then roll out with sugar and cinnamon.
Cut out like a pizza, then roll each piece together, starting at wide end, forming a horn.
Put in pan and bake at 350°F until golden brown.
Remove from pan right after baking.
Put upside down to cool.

title: great grandma's macaroni and cheese
directions: Grate cheese and set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon butter to water to	cook
macaroni.
Cook
for
9 minutes and drain.
To make sauce,
melt
butter
on low heat.	Stir in flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt
and
pepper.	Turn
up
heat and cook flour and butter for 2
minutes,
stirring, but do not brown (this prevents
starchy taste).
Add
milk	all at once, stirring constantly.
When slightly thickened, take off heat and cover.

title: orange cooler salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Blend in frozen orange juice.
Pour into serving containers.
Refrigerate about 15 minutes.
Stir in oranges. Let congeal.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter and roll in crushed Wheaties. Sprinkle heavily with lemon pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pan fried fish
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge fish fillet in this. Combine egg and milk; dip fish in milk and then in breadcrumbs. Melt the margarine in a nonstick skillet; fry fillets 5 minutes on each side until golden brown.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage and onion until sausage is brown and onion is tender; drain.
Stir in apples, sauerkraut, water, brown sugar and caraway seed.
Transfer to a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: aunt helen myhre's sour cream raisin pie(from her award winning norske nook restaurant in osseo, wi)
directions: Stir sour cream and egg yolks together in heavy saucepan.
Add sugar, flour, then raisins and mix with a wooden spoon.
Cook over medium heat until raisins plump and filling is glossy (about 5 minutes or so).
Cool filling, slightly, then pour into cooled crust.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare meringue and spread on pie. Bake 15 to 20 minutes until peaks are golden brown.
Cool.
Keep in cool room or eat.
Refrigerate only if keeping overnight.

title: fried corn with bacon
directions: Slice corn off of cob and scrape cob to release the milk.
Set aside.
Place bacon in a large, deep skillet.
Cook over medium high heat until evenly brown.
Crumble and set aside.
Retain 2 tablespoons of the bacon grease in the pan and fry pepper until just softened.
Add the corn and cook until tender.
Stir in the crumbled bacon and cook 1 minute more.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, nuts and mashed bananas. Sift and add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Makes 1 loaf.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until thin.
Pour over cereal and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chips on top and bake at 350° until the chips melt.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine, and 3 Tbsp. of sugar.
Press into a 9 X 13 inch pyrex dish.
Bake at 375 for 6 minutes.
Do not let pretzels burn.
Cool.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Bake 30 minutes.
Crush 1 package or Ritz crackers and mix with 1/2 stick of margarine.
Sprinkle on top and brown.

title: olde english chess pie
directions: Soak currants in hot water until plump.
Drain.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Spread currants evenly over pastry.
Beat together sugar, flour, salt, mace, vanilla, sour cream, buttermilk and egg yolks.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into pie pan and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for an additional 25 minutes.

title: venus soup
directions: Bring water to a boil with onion.
Add orzo, bouillon, hamburg, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Boil for 20 minutes on medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Add Veg-All, including liquid.
Boil 10 minutes longer.
Season to taste.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna according to directions on box.
Cool some by running cold water over it.
Cook hamburger meat until done. Drain water and fat off meat.
Saute onion in oil.
Mix soup, spaghetti sauce, water, onions and hamburger meat in large pot. Simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly; it will scorch fast.
Layer noodles, sauce and Monterey Jack cheese in large baking pan or dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and bake at 400° until nice and brown.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels and milk over double boiler or heavy saucepan. It can be melted in a microwave, but be careful not to scorch. Add pecans; mix well.
Chill until it becomes easier to work with. Drop by teaspoons onto greased wax paper.
Insert toothpicks and freeze.
Melt chocolate in microwave if you prefer, with 1 tablespoon Crisco shortening.
Dip caramel and pecans into chocolate; place on wax paper to harden.
Remove small amounts from freezer to prevent them from thawing before they can be dipped.

title: lemon bisk pudding
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 18 to 25 minutes.
Beat the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip.
Put on top of baked layer.
Mix lemon pudding with milk.
Pour on top of second layer. Put a topping of Cool Whip on top of third layer.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: *pecan pie*
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add all ingredients and blend.
Turn mixture into unbaked pie shells and bake at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes or until brown and slightly firm.

title: chocolate eclair torte
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil.
Add flour.
Beat until smooth (until ball forms).
Cool 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Spread on greased jelly roll pan (or 9 x 13-inch pan).
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 425°.
When cool, press down and fill.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Stir in Cool Whip. Put on crust and chill.
When set, frost.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together and form into meatballs.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream
together
at
room temperature the cream cheese, margarine
and
Crisco.
Add
powdered sugar, German chocolate (melted in	hot water before you start mixing cake), eggs (one at a
time),
plain
flour,
vanilla extract, baking soda and salt. Alternate
flour ingredients with buttermilk, beginning and ending
with flour.
Bake in 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, crumbs, parsley flakes, eggs, soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder, catsup and onion.
Blend well.
Form into small balls.
Arrange in 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
In medium saucepan, combine cranberry sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice, stirring occasionally until smooth and sauce is melted.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes.
Makes about 60 meatballs.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator; roll into small balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute beef and onion in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and celery salt.
Spoon into shallow baking dish.
Spread mashed potatoes on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, uncovered, until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbly.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place ingredients in layers.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: hamburgers
directions: Mix hamburger and onions together.
Make hamburger patties. Fry until done.
Top with cheese.

title: di's baked bread
directions: Slice your French bread in two halves.
Spread with cream cheese, parsley flakes and touch of garlic powder.
Slice tomatoes and cut slices in half.
Lay slices down the length
of bread. Sprinkle heavily with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until cheese melts. Serve hot.

title: oven meal
directions: Put all ingredients in baking pan or casserole in order given. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.	Serves 6.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend the butter, brown sugar, 1 cup of the flour and the walnuts until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Press all but 1/2 cup of the mixture into the bottom of a 9-inch square pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden around the edges.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Fry hamburger until brown.
Drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook about 1/2 hour until seasoned.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Cut bread in 1-inch thick squares, not through bottom of crust.
Stuff with mushrooms and Swiss cheese.
Melt the remaining ingredients together on the stove and pour over bread.
Wrap bread well in foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: my e-z sweet pickles
directions: Add sugar or sweetener to pickles. Store in refrigerator. Allow 2 to 3 days to set to blend flavors.
Vary amount of sweetener to your preference.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into refrigerator for a couple of hours.
Serve with plain tortilla chips.

title: rich pound cake
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, let egg whites warm to room temperature, about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour 10-inch tube pan.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat egg whites until foamy at high speed with electric mixer.
Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar, 1/4 cup at a time, beating after each addition.
Continue beating until soft peaks form when beater is slowly raised.
Turn in medium bowl.

title: old world pizza crust
directions: Heat water and oil to 120°.
In a large mixing bowl combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, yeast, salt and warm water mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and knead for three minutes.
If dough is sticky, knead in enough of the remaining 1/2 cup flour to form a stiff dough.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and allow to rise in warm place until double in size (about 40 minutes.)
Punch down and turn until a lightly floured board; divide in half.
Roll each into a 13-inch circle.
Place on 2 lightly greased 12-inch pizza pans.
Fold edge over to form a ridge.
Prick bottom with fork.
Par-bake crusts in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Add filling and continue baking 20 minutes.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Mix dry ingredients in small heavy saucepan.
GRADUALLY add water and vinegar.
Stir in raisins and cook on low heat until a syrup forms.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour in a baking dish and bake for 35 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in frypan.
Add onions, celery, salt, pepper and water.
Cook until meat is tender.
Add rest of ingredients; cook about 2 1/2 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits; roll in cinnamon and sugar that have been mixed together. Put in greased bundt pan. Melt oleo; add brown sugar and water; boil 2 minutes and pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Optional: Place nuts in bottom of pan before adding biscuits.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Coat baking dish with 1 teaspoon oil (bottom and sides of 13 x 2 x 5-inch or other size dish).
With rolling pan, roll 1 package of crescent rolls to line bottom and sides of baking dish.
Layer alternately corned beef, cheese, sauce and sauerkraut, two or three times.
Roll second Pillsbury dough to very thin crust.
Top with optional milk.
Bake in 350° oven 10 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift
and
mix	together dry ingredients in mixing dish and make
holes.
Put
in
liquid ingredients and mix well. Place in	a 13 x 9-inch dish baking pan (greased and floured). Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili rellenos dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Drain.
Serve with Doritos or corn chips.
(Better if made a day ahead.)

title: sweet and sour chops
directions: Mix flour, beer and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Should be thick. Lightly salt chops with batter.
Fry in 1-inch hot oil.
Drain.

title: noodle broccoli cheese soup
directions: Heat butter. Add garlic, onion and broccoli.
Stir in chicken broth, heated milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Do not boil. Add cooked noodles.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill for about an hour.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.

title: punch
directions: Blend first 2 ingredients; add pineapple and 7-Up.

title: crab pizza(appetizer)
directions: Mix the cream cheese, onion and horseradish, if desired. Spread on platter, leaving a 1-inch space all around edge of platter. Spread chili sauce on top of cream cheese mixture. Break up crabmeat and spread on top. Sprinkle dried parsley on top of crabmeat. Circle platter with Ritz crackers.

title: corn deluxe
directions: Mix egg, 3/4 cup cheese, green pepper, half and half, onion, corn, salt and pepper.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix corn flakes, butter and cheese.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Add to pie shell and bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes, until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except stuffing mix in a large mixing bowl. Add salt and pepper to taste. Spread in 3-quart ovenproof dish or 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with more poppy seed and top with 1/2 bag of stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef & rice skillet
directions: Mix together and lightly brown the ground beef, butter salt and pepper.
Thinly slice the onion and green pepper and add to skillet.
Stir in rice and saute over high heat until rice is lightly browned.
Add tomatoes and mustard, mix well.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: microwave sweet pickles
directions: In a small bowl, combine salt, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed, vinegar and sugar.
Mix cucumbers and onion in microwavable bowl.
Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers and onion.

title: bacon and egg souffle casserole
directions: Fry bacon until lightly brown; dice.
Brush bread with bacon drippings; cut in pieces.
Put in casserole alternate layers of bread and bacon.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over bread.
Set dish in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk 5 minutes. Add butter, salt and sugar. Pour slowly over eggs. Add vanilla and mix well. Pour into greased baking dish and bake in pan of hot water at 350° until firm, approximately 1 hour. (Add 1/2 cup raisins, if desired before baking.) Serves 8.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans, in a medium size saucepan; stir well.
Place over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Continue to cook until thermometer (candy) registers about 220°.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans, stirring until well coated.
Spread pecans on waxed paper and separate with a fork.
Cool.
Yields 4 cups.

title: wiener and bean pot casserole
directions: Use uniformly sized potatoes.
Scrub, dry and prick in several places with fork.
On double layer of paper toweling, microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, plus 1 to 2 minutes each additional potato.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Combine the Bisquick, milk and cheese.
Beat until well mixed. This mixture will be thick.
If you think it is too thick, add a little more milk.
Pinch off portions and roll in the palms of your hands to about the size of golf balls. Flatten slightly.
Dip each biscuit in the garlic butter and place on baking sheet, spacing them about 1 inch apart. Bake for about 10 minutes. Remove from oven and brush tops with remaining garlic butter.
Return to oven and bake an additional 4 to 5 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm. Makes about 8 biscuits.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Prepare 2 cups biscuit mix with milk according to directions on box.
Roll into a rectangle.
Crumble and spread sausage over biscuit rectangle.
Roll up jelly roll fashion, the long way. Place in freezer.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer 1/2 hour before slicing thinly.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheets at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: eggplant
directions: Peel and cube eggplant; boil in salted water for 5 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Put 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Saute garlic for one minute.
Add onions and green pepper.
Saute until wilted, about 5 minutes.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Add 4 tablespoons oil, the oregano and eggplant to skillet.
Sprinkle with brown sugar; heat for 10 minutes, stirring the eggplant so it cooks evenly.
Remove from heat.

title: tropical baked beans
directions: Drain pineapple reserving 1/2 c. juice.
Combine reserved juice, pineapple, baked beans, hot dogs, ketchup, sugar and mustard. Pour into 2 qt. casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: texas cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour and salt thoroughly, then add remaining ingredients (without mixing).
Grease heavy, iron skillet well. Stir the mixture thoroughly and pour into the hot pans.
Bake at 450° until done.
The bread will be moist and brown on the bottom.

title: sweet and sour asparagus
directions: Mix first seven ingredients bring to a boil.
Place asparagus in glass dish and pour boiling mixture over.
Let sit in refrigerator 24 hours, grate 2 or 3 hard cooked eggs over.

title: quiche
directions: Grease pie plate and place cheese in bottom.
Place bread on top of cheese.
Beat eggs and milk; add salt and dry mustard.
Add bacon or mushrooms and pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Also great with broccoli or crabmeat.

title: dirt cake
directions: Follow the directions with pudding.
Crunch Oreos.
Form a layer on the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix pudding, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla flavor.
Mix until smooth and thick. Pour over crunched Oreos and add another layer of Oreos on top of the mixed items.
Spread Cool Whip, then sprinkle leftover Oreos as a decoration.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes.

title: pecan ice cream
directions: In medium saucepan, bring milk to boil with vanilla bean and pecans. Remove from heat and cover. Let infuse for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground chuck in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Add finely chopped onion and saute until tender.
Drain green beans.
Add to beef.
Add 1/2 cup of green bean juice.
Add 3 cans of tomato sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour in casserole dish.
Boil and mash peeled potatoes with hand mixer. Add 1/4 cup milk and whip.
Spoon potatoes over top of beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with cottage cheese and tossed green salad.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble bread; put in bottom of a large casserole dish. Crumble cooked sausage or preferred meat; place on top of bread. Put cheese on top of bread and meat.
Whip eggs with all other ingredients; pour over mixture.
Bake in a 350° to 400° oven for about 45 minutes, or until done in center.
Serves approximately 10 people.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Clean and core strawberries.
Put in cold water.

Drain, then put the berries, sugar and lemon juice in a 6-quart pot. Stir just to dissolve the sugar. When starts to boil, turn to medium or low heat so it won't boil over. Cook for 1 hour until candy thermometer reads 224°.
Put into jars.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken, soup, broth and peas and carrots. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix butter, milk, baking powder and flour. Pour over chicken mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until crust rises and browns.

title: new york special milk punch
directions: Add all ingredients together in a large bowl and beat until frothy.
Pour into chilled punch bowl.
Makes 3 quarts.
Serves about 25.

title: chili potato puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Mash well with butter, evaporated milk, salt and egg. Stir in green chilies.
Beat well.
Using ice cream scoop, scoop out potatoes onto a well-greased baking sheet.
With handle of a teaspoon, make a hollow place in the scoop and fill with a cheese cube.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve the puffs with chopped parsley and garnish with slice of tomato, if desired. Serves 13.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour and set aside.
Mix butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs, gradually, and flour.
Mix then add chocolate chips and nuts. Spread into greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar and melted butter. Add syrup; mix with a fork. Fold in whipped cream and vanilla. Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until firm.

title: classic green bean casserole
directions: Arrange 1/2 of the green beans, soup and onion rings in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Repeat, using remaining ingredients.
Cover. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: crab pizza
directions: Layer 1:
Add together and beat with mixer the cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, mayonnaise, onion, salt and dash of garlic.
Spread in glass dish.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, pumpkin, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together and add flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Blend together and drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet (do not flatten).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with graham crackers.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup in a saucepan.
Stir over low heat until butter is melted and mixture comes to a slow simmer.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
Blend in spices and sour cream.
Add soda and flour a little at a time until well blended.
The dough will be soft.
Shape into a roll; wrap well and refrigerate overnight or as long as a week.
Unused portions can be frozen.

title: delicious fruit dip
directions: Blend together and chill.
Use fruit of your choice for dipping.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine the first three ingredients, then add eggs and oil. Add just enough milk until moist and able to roll.
Flour counter and roll until thin (dough will be stiff), then cut into 2-inch strips.
Drop into boiling chicken broth.
Cook until done.

title: angel food cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars until creamy.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Then mix into sugar mixture.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Spread on a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: italian cheese ball
directions: Spread salad dressing mix on wax paper.
Place cream cheese on mix.
Turn to coat sides, top and bottom.
Place on cheese board and serve with crackers.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put tomato slices in to marinate in refrigerator a few hours before serving.
Delicious on sandwiches, in salads, or alone.

title: impossible pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle nuts in 10-inch pie plate.
Beat with hand mixer on high for 1 minute the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven until set.

title: sponge cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs until very light. Beat in sugar, salt and vanilla.
Heat butter in hot milk and beat in the mixture.
Sift together flour and baking powder and add to cake batter and beat very quickly.
Immediately pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shred cheese.
Finely chop peppers and onion, squeezing out excess juice.
Mince garlic.
Mix all ingredients.
Form into a ball and roll in pecans.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs with spoon.
Add flour, sugar and fruit cocktail. Mix and pour into pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Boil ribs in water for 20 to 30 minutes; drain.
Rinse with cool water.
Place in a crock-pot.
Combine ketchup and cola (makes a delicious barbecue sauce); pour over ribs.
Cook on high for 5 to 6 hours, uncovered.
Baste occasionally.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add tomato soup and beans; stir. Grease casserole dish and layer meat mixture and potatoes.
Top with cheese.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat thoroughly.
For slaw, fruit salads and carrot salad.
Chill.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream butter and gradually beat in the sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add the mashed bananas and mix well.
Blend in the sifted dry ingredients and fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave at High speed for 4 minutes.
Stir and cook 4 minutes more.
Add margarine and vanilla to first ingredients. Microwave for 1 minute.
Add soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto sheet of aluminum foil.
Let cool 1 hour.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in drained pineapple juice. Add softened cream cheese, salad dressing and strawberries. Cool. When thickened, fold in Cool Whip and pineapple. Pour into flat dish. Freeze.

title: north carolina style cole slaw
directions: Bring sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper to a boil.
Place cabbage, onion, bell pepper and pimento in a gallon jar.
Pour dressing over vegetables, refrigerate.
Keeps several weeks.

title: carrots with glaze
directions: Peel and quarter carrots; steam until tender. Mix the mustard, butter and brown sugar in a small bowl, then stir into cooked carrots. Cook until carrots are glazed.

title: rainbow sherbet punch
directions: Break up sherbet into small chunks and allow to soften.
Pour in ginger ale or Seven-Up.
Add cherries and cherry juice for color if you wish.

title: crab meat appetizer
directions: Blend cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion and garlic salt by hand and spread on a shallow plate.
Pour a bottle of chili sauce on the spread.
Layer the crab meat on top of the sauce.
Sprinkle the top with fresh parsley.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Stir together cornstarch, sugar and cocoa.
Add cold milk. Do not stir.
Put in microwave and cook 3 minutes on High.
Then stir to mix well.
Return to the microwave for 5 more minutes on High.
Remove and stir well to blend.
Beat about 1/3 of the mixture slowly into the 3 beaten egg yolks, until they look chocolaty and are steaming.
Return the yolk mixture to the remaining filling and mix well.
Cook on High 2 minutes.
Remove and stir.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into the cooked shell.
Beat egg whites with 2 or 3 tablespoons sugar and brown at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake(easy)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pack 2/3 of mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix next 3 ingredients and spread over bottom layer. Put other 1/3 of mixture over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Chop onion, green pepper, celery and apple.
Mix with pimiento and sauerkraut.
Add dressing; toss well.
Chill and drain before serving.
Dressing may be saved and used again.
Keeps well.

title: toffee pieces
directions: Place crackers on bottom of a buttered 2-quart glass baking dish. Set aside.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Beat eggs with sugar with electric mixer until creamy.
Add oil gradually.
Add vanilla and apples.
Fold in flour mixture and nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Test center for doneness.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure flour, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, the baking powder and salt into bowl.
Blend in milk and shortening; stir in nuts.
Pour into ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Stir together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 45 minutes.
While hot, cut into squares; invert each onto dessert plate and spoon sauce over each serving.
Makes 9 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg.
Beat well.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add hot water.
Mix until well blended.
Add chocolate pieces, nuts and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: hot buttered rum mix
directions: In large heavy pot, place 1 pound butter (not margarine), ice cream, brown sugar and white sugar.
Melt very slowly over low heat, stirring often.
When completely melted, add vanilla.
Cool and place in covered freezer container.

title: wild rice and chicken casserole
directions: Mix altogether; place in greased casserole dish.
Cook 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream oleo; add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Mix in molasses, nuts and warm water.
Mix soda with small amount of flour.
Add to mixture.
Stir in remaining flour.
Knead with hands until dough sticks together.
Divide dough into 2 parts; shape into rolls.
Put in wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Slice on floured board.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: aunt teri's biscuits
directions: Mix 2 cups flour and powdered buttermilk.
Add mayonnaise and water; knead until mixture is blended well.
Form a dough ball in middle of bowl.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of flour over dough.
Shake bowl side to side to allow flour to coat bowl.
This will keep dough from sticking to the sides.
Grease baking sheet.
Pinch a small amount of dough and roll into a ball, using the palm of your hand. Place ball on baking sheet; flatten with fingers.
Repeat the last two steps until all the dough has been used.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.
Butter tops and bottoms.

title: pan dessert
directions: Crumble together first 3 ingredients; pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool.
Mix together powdered sugar, 1/2 of a 9 ounce Cool Whip and cream cheese. Spread on crust.
Mix the pudding and spread on the above.
Spread rest of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a buttered 9 by 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover each breast with a slice of cheese.
Mix can of soup with water according to directions on can.
Pour this over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle croutons evenly over soup.
Drizzle croutons with melted butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: brown sugar
directions: Blend sugar and molasses together.
Yields 1/2 cup brown sugar.

title: barbecued trout
directions: Place trout in a single layer in a plastic bag or glass baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over trout.
Let stand 1 hour, turning once.
Remove fish, reserving marinade. Place fish in a single layer in a well-greased hinged wire grill basket.
Grill, covered, over medium coals for 8 to 10 minutes or until fish is browned on the bottom.
Turn and baste with marinade.
Grill 5 to 7 minutes longer or until fish flakes with a fork.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, butter and salt for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Put over popped corn.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: crustless pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate with a little oil.
Combine all ingredients, except egg whites.
Blend until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cranberry nut coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternating with sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Grease a tube pan.
Pour half the batter on the bottom.
Spread 1/2 of whole cranberry sauce on top.
Pour rest of batter and then rest of cranberry sauce.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Prepare glaze.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Add 1/2 cup milk and 3 1/2 cups flour; mix.
Then add 1/2 cup flour with baking powder.
Add the other 1/2 cup milk and vanilla with the baking soda.

title: nut filled cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, egg and vanilla together.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well and roll into small balls the size of a walnut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make a hole in center and fill with filling.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs and add milk.
Sift flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add milk and egg mixture.
Beat until smooth. Holding your finger over bottom of funnel, pour batter into funnel; drop batter into hot (375°) oil, swirling it into circles from center out.
Make each about 6 inches in diameter.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on brown paper.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: reese's chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips and nuts, if desired. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
(Do not overbake; cookies will be soft.
They will puff while baking and flatten when cooling.)
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Mix cabbage and cracker crumbs and place in a casserole dish. Put in oven that has been heated to 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cabbage wilts.
Melt margarine.
Add pepper and milk; heat to scalding point.
Pour over wilted cabbage.
Return to oven and continue cooking about 50 minutes longer or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Good hot or cold.

title: strawberry graham torte
directions: In large bowl, mix 1/2 cup of the sugar and the oil.
Stir in the berries and nuts.
In small bowl, beat whites until soft peaks form (tips curl).
Slowly add rest of sugar until stiff peaks form (tips stand straight).
Gently fold in berry mixture.
Cover bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with 9 graham cracker squares. Spread 1/3 berry mixture, then crackers, then berries.
Repeat until all is gone.
Top with 9 crackers.
Chill overnight.
Spread with whipped cream and the crumbs just before serving.
Note:
For easy cutting, chill overnight.

title: salmon steaks with lemon dill sauce
directions: Rinse salmon with cold water and pat dry.
Place salmon steaks in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; arrange onion slices over salmon.
Combine water, 1 tablespoon lemon juice, bouillon granules and dill weed; pour over salmon.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until steaks flake easily when tested with a fork.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup cooking liquid; discard onion. Transfer salmon steaks to a serving platter and keep warm.

title: red lobster rolls
directions: Combine flour, milk and cheese with wooden spoon until soft dough forms, then beat 30 seconds.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoonfuls onto greased iron skillet.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix butter, garlic and parsley together and brush on warm rolls.

title: my strawberry bread
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: little river fry bread(makes 4 servings; prep time: 15 minutes)
directions: Bring water to a boil; dampen 1/2 cup meal with cold water. Stir into boiling water until thick.
Cool.
Add yeast, baking powder, salt, sugar and flour.
Mix until real stiff.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down and let rise again.
Fry.

title: louisiana corn bread(lemon cake)
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: larisa's hearty lamb and rice
directions: Heat the oil in a very large skillet (that has a cover); the heat setting should be a little over medium.
When the oil is very hot, add the lamb, stirring periodically.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes.
Add the rice.
Cover.
Lower the heat to a setting between low and medium.
Let this continue cooking for 30 minutes, stirring periodically.
If the dish begins to dry out, add additional oil.

title: turkey in a sack
directions: Combine pepper, salt, paprika and hot water.
Let stand at least 10 minutes.
Add peanut oil and mix thoroughly.
Wash and dry turkey.
Rub some peanut oil mixture into inside and outside of turkey.
Truss as desired.
Pour remaining oil and additional oil into large paper grocery sack (heavy-duty type).
Rub oil into inside of sack until all of sack is sealed with oil mixture. Place turkey in sack, breast up.
Fold over end of the sack and tie securely.
Bake in moderate oven (325°) for approximately 10 minutes per pound.

title: baked ham and cheesewich
directions: Lightly flour a pastry cloth or a piece of wax paper.
Place bread dough on cloth; sprinkle lightly with flour.
Roll out dough to a 10 x 14-inch rectangle.
Spread mustard lengthwise down center 1/3 of dough.
Top with ham, then cheese and spinach.
Make cuts in dough from filling to dough edges at 1 inch intervals along sides of filling.
Alternating sides, fold cup strips at a slight angle over top of filling to cover.
Carefully transfer filled dough loaf to a greased baking sheet.
Let rise for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush loaf with egg white.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm; cut into slices.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add the sour cream, flour, baking powder, baking soda and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix the cinnamon, walnuts and brown sugar. Grease and flour large pan (hole in middle).
Add 1/2 of batter to pan; sprinkle with 1/2 of nut mixture.
Add remaining batter; sprinkle with remaining nut mixture on top.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: sweet and sour cocktail sausages
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, heat the soup, jelly, vinegar and Worcestershire until jelly melts and mixture is very warm.
Meanwhile, place 1 sausage and 1 chunk of pineapple on a toothpick.
Add to sauce.
Heat through, stirring occasionally. Serve hot.
Makes about 40 appetizers.

title: fay's easy raspberry squares
directions: Prepare pie crust, roll to fit greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400 degrees for 5 - 10 minutes, until light brown.

title: peppered steak
directions: Combine last 5 ingredients.
Marinate steak in sauce overnight, turning once.
Grill on each side for 20 minutes for medium well.
Slice in thin slices and serve immediately.

title: cheesy chicken wings
directions: Wash chicken wings. Pat dry.
In a bowl, combine the crumbled crackers or bread crumbs, herbs and Parmesan cheese.
Add seasonings and mix well.
Melt butter.
Dip chicken wings first in butter, then in bread crumbs.
Place chicken wings in baking dish. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until lightly brown or done. Serves 4 people.

title: grandma's filled sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and lard (Crisco), sour cream, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add flour.
Roll dough to desired thickness. Fill and press edges together with fork.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until slightly brown at 350°.

title: pistachio fluff
directions: Mix pineapple and pistachio pudding with spoon.
Stir in miniature marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Must refrigerate overnight. It makes it very light and fluffy.

title: prune cream cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs (beaten) and sour cream; add rolled oats.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and mace.
Combine the dry ingredients with rolled oats; add to sugar and shortening mixture.
Add and beat in thoroughly the prunes (cut into pieces).
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 425°.

title: hot 'n spicy black-eyed peas and rice
directions: Place water, peas, ham, celery, onion, garlic powder, chili powder, cayenne and black pepper in large deep cooking pot. Cover and simmer about 1 hour and 30 minutes or until peas are tender. Add more water as needed. Stir in rice and tomato paste. Cover. Let stand to heat thoroughly before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: bavarian mint chippers
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add mint extract and dissolved coffee.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in chips and almonds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, soy sauce, pepper, beans, and 2/3 cup onions. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes, stir and sprinkle remaining 2/3 cups onions over bean mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: cubed steak
directions: Sprinkle steak with garlic salt, roll in flour.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons of oil in skillet and brown steak on both sides. Place in greased casserole dish.
Combine soup, catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and brown sugar.
Pour this over steak and cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place layer of asparagus tips in casserole dish.
Cover with 1 sliced egg and 1/8 pound grated cheese.
Use remaining asparagus, egg and cheese in the same manner.
Top with the can of mushroom soup.
Place cracker crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp cream cheese dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Put cream cheese in bowl and pour shrimp mixture over it. Serve with crackers.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking soda, baking powder, salt, sugar and spices and sift again.
Cut in shortening.
Add raisins.
Add enough sour milk to make a stiff dough.
Turn onto floured board.
Knead slightly.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Place close together in shallow pan.
With sharp knife, cut a cross in each roll.
Brush with a solution of milk and sugar.
Bake in hot oven (475°) for 20 minutes.
Brush again with sugar and milk solution.
Fill cross with plain frosting.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 buns.

title: delicious crab cakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Serve with crab cakes.

title: peach punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients, except ginger ale.
Cool and when ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken until meat comes off bone.
In skillet, saute onion, pepper and celery until transparent.
Debone chicken, cut into pieces and add to vegetables.
Add stewed tomatoes and rice. Add broth from chicken to own desired thickness.
Salt and pepper to taste; sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: golden turkey bake
directions: Combine cornflakes with melted butter.
Set aside for topping. Stir together remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into 10 x 6 x 2-inch quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Mix spinach and onion with cottage cheese.
Fold in egg white. Pour into small baking pan
and
bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil
chicken in water with chopped celery, onion and a dash of	poultry
seasoning.
When cooked, remove bones, skin and fat. Add meat to broth.	Add chicken soup base (dissolved in
4 to 5 cups
warm water), rice, barley, potatoes, carrots, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until cooked.

title: green fluff
directions: Make pudding as directed on box.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: hurry up casserole
directions: Layer vegetables then meat on top.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice onion and cucumbers in dish.
Salt and pepper to taste. Combine all other ingredients, adding sugar as needed.
Pour mix over cucumbers and stir well.
Let set an hour or longer before serving.

title: stir-fry vegetables and chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add Oriental vegetables and water chestnuts.
Stir-fry until tender.
Add soy sauce and garlic salt. Stir in mixture of cornstarch and enough water to cover vegetables.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in chicken.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Put oatmeal in mixing bowl and add boiling water and margarine.
Let set for 20 minutes.
Add slightly beaten eggs and beat.
Add vanilla and both sugars.
Beat well and add soda, salt, spices and flour.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix
all together.
Pour into 2 pie
shells.
Top
with the other 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for about
35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg whites, honey and oil.
Mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups almost full.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Microwave broccoli in a microwave-safe bowl, following package directions; drain. Add cheese and 2 tablespoons butter to broccoli. Microwave on High for 2 minutes, until cheese is melted, stirring once or twice.

title: homemade breakfast sausage
directions: Mix all spices together in a small bowl.
Sprinkle over turkey in a large mixing bowl.
Knead together with hands until well mixed.
Shape into patties and fry.
Freeze what is unused.
One makes a large batch and divide into smaller packages to freeze.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix and bake in pie shell at 400° until thick in center.

title: cooney corn soup
directions: Rinse meat off; season with salt and pepper or seasoned salt and pepper.
Brown meat in oil in Dutch oven pot or soup pot. When brown, put onion and potatoes in with meat and cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Crush whole tomatoes and add them, the tomato sauce, the corn, 1 teaspoon garlic and a dash of red pepper.
Add about 1 cup of water.
Cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally.
May need to add more water as it cooks.
May serve over rice or eat with crackers.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel and cut onions into very thin slices.
Melt butter and oil in a large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add onions and simmer over low heat about 15 minutes.
Sprinkle salt and sugar over onions. Raise heat to moderate and cook about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until onions are tender and have turned an even, golden brown.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs together with the sugar until light and well blended. Add the oil; continue to beat.
Sift or stir the dry ingredients together and thoroughly beat them into the egg mixture.
Add pumpkin, mixing well again.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes, then turn out on rack to cool.
Serve plain or frost with cream cheese icing.

title: granny's pound cake
directions: Mix all together and beat well.
Cook at 300 degrees about 1 hour.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in a baking dish and fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs. Bake potatoes at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned, cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft inside. Check with a fork.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain juice from beans.
In a medium bowl, mix beans with onion, chopped eggs and pickle relish, then mix in mayonnaise. Chill until ready to serve.

title: blushing frappe
directions: Puree the berries with the rest of the ingredients, except ice.
Pour over crushed ice in frosty glasses and serve with straws.
Serves 6.

title: williamsburg cheese soup
directions: Into a 5-quart pot, place water, bouillon cubes, onion, celery and potatoes.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 10 minutes.
Add broccoli, cauliflower, mushroom soup, Velveeta cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook several hours, 5 or more, on simmer.
Stir often so cheese doesn't rise to the top.
(May use cream of potato soup and your choice of vegetables, fresh or frozen).
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring rice, milk, and sugar to boil.
Simmer for 45 minutes. Then slowly blend in eggs, heavy cream and vanilla which have been beaten together.
Heat until mixture starts to thicken.
Add raisins if desired.
Top with cinnamon.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: After chopping, mix nuts and fruits together with a little flour to separate lumps and make easy to handle.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well, then add flour, sifted with spices alternately with water and soda mixture.
If desired, add 3 tablespoons of sherry to soda mixture.
Combine batter and fruit mixture in large pan using hands to mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 20 to 30 minutes or until medium brown in color.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix together dates, sugar and eggs and boil, medium heat, 5 minutes in heavy kettle.
Remove from fire and add butter and vanilla.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into coconut and shape into balls.
Store in air tight container.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Drain juice from pineapple and add.
Grate rind of one orange and add juice of both oranges.
Add to gelatin; mix.
Cool.
When begins to thicken, add fruit and place in mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and ready to serve.

title: champagne salad
directions: Soften and blend cream cheese with sugar.
Mix together drained pineapple, strawberries, bananas, nuts and whipped topping. Combine the two mixtures.
Put into loaf pan or 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze.
Take out awhile before eating.
Better if not frozen solid.

title: beet pickles
directions: Simmer 15 minutes; place sliced beets in mixture;
heat and can.
Be sure to
slice
every beet.
Mixture should can 8 pints.

title: fried okra
directions: Slice okra about 1/4-inch thick circles. Place in brown paper bag with equal amounts of flour and cornmeal, enough to cover. Shake well.
Pour bacon grease in large skillet and get it hot. Add okra.
Fry and turn often until crispy.

title: sugar-free blueberry pie
directions: Follow directions for pudding.
Remove from heat and add 2 cups of blueberries.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell or cooked pie shell.
When cooled, top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and hot water until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Pour 1/3 of syrup into well beaten egg whites.
Beat well.
Allow the syrup to cook while beating.
Add the second third of syrup in the same manner.
Allow the last third to boil while beating.
Finally add the last third of syrup and beat until ready to pour into a buttered dish.
Flavor to suit taste.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown meat, drain fat.
Add taco seasoning, tomato paste and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Press biscuits together in a pie pan.
Top with half the meat, then half of the cheese; repeat.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with sour cream or salsa.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove and let cool.
Add noodles to chicken broth and cook until tender.
Take chicken off bones and cut into small pieces.
Remove noodles from broth.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add some broth so it will be moist.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees until cheese has melted.

title: lush dessert pie
directions: Melt oleo. Add flour and chopped nuts.
Mix well. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.
Mix powdered sugar, 1 cup Cool Whip and cream cheese until smooth. Spread over the baked mixture.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk. Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: banana zucchini bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add bananas.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in egg mixture.
Add pecans.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown beef and sausage together; drain. Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder. (Add cheese last.) Cook slowly until cheese is melted. Spread mixture on rye bread. Place on cookie sheet and freeze. When frozen, may be put in airtight container.

title: skillet chicken dinner
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook onions in oil until golden.
Remove with slotted spoon to bowl.
On sheet of waxed paper, mix flour, salt, dried rosemary and pepper to coat chicken thighs.
In remaining oil in skillet over medium-high heat, cook chicken until golden brown on all sides.

title: cherry streusel(in microwave)
directions: Spread pie filling in ungreased round glass baking dish (8 1/4 x 1 1/2-inch).
Sprinkle cake mix (dry) over filling.
Mix nuts, cinnamon and brown sugar in a small bowl.
Sprinkle over cake mix. Microwave margarine until melted, drizzle over mixture in dish. Microwave uncovered 8 minutes at bake (80% power) turn dish 1/4 turn.
Microwave until mixture is bubbly and topping is almost firm, about another 8 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Makes a delicious dessert.
Other pie fillings may be used.
Apple is very good.

title: oreo cream pie
directions: Spread 1 qt. Oreo ice cream into Oreo pie crust. Top with 4 oz. cool whip. Drizzle 2 Tbsp. chocolate syrup over cool whip. Cover and freeze until firm.

title: meatless meatburgers
directions: Add all ingredients; mix well.
Make burgers.
Bake on greased baking sheet or can be fried.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and drain. In a large pot, bring 9 cups of water to a boil. Add rice to water when boiling and cook for 7 minutes. Remove from heat. Add to rice and water the sausage, soup packages and vegetables. Stir all together. Then place mixture in casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350°. Make for a large crowd. This recipe can be cut in half.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients together.
Mix in rice and bring to a full boil.

title: yogurt-berry parfaits
directions: Spoon yogurt into individual dessert glasses.
Top with fresh berries.
Yield:
2 to 3 servings.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook
rice
and
set aside.
Chop "raw" giblets, ground beef and
chicken
liver
in a blender or food processor or by hand. Combine
all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix lightly. Add to a large pot.	(Add a little oil or use a nonstick pot.) Cook under medium heat for about 45 minutes.
Afterwards, add cooked rice and
let
simmer
for about 10 minutes.
Add more rice if
not thick enough.
This will serve 10.	Can be eaten alone or with chicken, barbecue or turkey.

title: mama's apple cake
directions: Mix eggs and oil.
Add sugar, flour and spices.
Add apples and nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
The mixture will get very thick.

title: chocolate fudge icing
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix the ingredients with an electric handmixer until stiff or fluffy.

title: easy homemade pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and let stand one hour at room temperature.
Place cut cucumber into jars.
Cover with liquid and let stand one week in refrigerator before using.
Will keep in refrigerator for three months.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Butter dish and put 1 cup croutons or stuffing in bottom.
Add remaining ingredients.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup croutons or stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oysters in bacon
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Wrap each oyster in a piece of bacon.
Arrange the wrapped oysters with bacon ends down on a rack in a shallow pan.
Bake only until the bacon is slightly browned. Drain on paper towels.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix pudding and crushed pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage bacon wrap
directions: Cut bacon in 1/3, cut links in 1/3.
Wrap bacon around sausage links.
Place toothpick in sausage securing bacon.
Place in 9-inch pie pan, pack box of brown ground bacon and sausage links. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Drain grease.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells.
Brown ground beef and garlic in large skillet.
Blend in the next 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Stir in beef.
Fill each manicotti with about 1/4 cup cheese-meat combination.
Place in single layer in baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining combination.
Cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make white sauce of first 4 ingredients.
Place the potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with sauce.
Cover casserole and bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 225° for 1 3/4 hours, stirring often.

title: orange salad
directions: Peel oranges and drain olives.
Put in medium bowl.
Season with pepper and toss in oil.

title: green punch
directions: Add pineapple, orange and lemon juices to Kool-Aid.
Add the ginger ale before serving.

title: cheese ring
directions: Shape into ring on serving platter.
Refrigerate overnight. Place strawberry preserves in center of ring.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: chocolate glaze(for all candy)
directions: Melt over simmering water in top of a double boiler; dip candies and then place on wax paper.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Add potato and eggs.
Place mixture in 6 heated flour tortillas.
Serve with picante sauce. Serves 6 to 8.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients, add raisins and nuts and add to creamed mixture. Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese with a twist
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cornstarch, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Add margarine.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium-high heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of cheese until melted.
Add macaroni.
Turn into greased casserole.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup of cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top. Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 25 minutes, until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: emerald chicken(china)
directions: Cut chicken into chunks.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a wok. Add chicken to the wok with ginger.
Stir and cook.
Stir in the onion and cook for a couple of minutes.
Add the remaining vegetables and cook for a few minutes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add the chicken broth, soy sauce, and rice wine. Cover and cook until the liquid boils.
Cook for 2 more minutes. Lower the heat and cook for 2-3 more minutes.
Mix the cornstarch with water and stir until smooth.
Increase the heat mix the vegetables and cook until it thickens.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds if desired.
Makes six servings.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, evaporated milk and vanilla. Mix well. Pour into ice cream freezer. Fill remainder with milk.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut all fruit bite size and add apples and bananas last. Cover all cut up fruit with the peach pie filling and stir it in.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix yeast with warm water, then add sugar, salt, softened oleo and 3 cups of flour.
Mix with mixer and add 1/2 cup more of flour. Knead 8 minutes.
Add flour until not sticky.
Place in greased bowl and cover for 1 hour to raise.
Ready for pizza sauce and bake.

title: lee's french dressing
directions: Mix all together and shake well.
Makes 1 pint.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 3-quart casserole; cover with zucchini slices.
Mix soup and curry.
Pour over chicken and zucchini.
Scatter cheese and crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Put vegetable oil in frypan over medium heat.
Add chicken; fry until white.
Remove and drain.
Partly cook broccoli; drain. Put in a casserole dish.
Add chicken.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cut in squares.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, flour, 7-Up and lemon flavor. Beat 5 minutes. Pour batter into 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until it is well done.

title: lazy lasagne
directions: Brown chuck.
Pour off fat and add water, puree and mix.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer.
Cover and cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with Mozzarella.
Place in oven and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple and carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots; save some liquid to use in final cooking. Butter casserole; put layers of carrots and sliced apples.
Dot with butter, sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Put some liquid in bottom of casserole (about 1/4 cup).
Bake covered about 45 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: butter wafers
directions: Cream butter or margarine until soft; gradually add 1 cup of sugar.
Blend together until light and creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift flour.
Stir the flour gradually into the butter mixture.
Shape dough into 1/2-inch balls.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 375° oven until the edges are light brown (about 8 minutes).
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and 1/2 cup cold milk.
Mix well. Scald remaining milk and add chocolate.
Stir until chocolate is melted.
Add scalded milk and chocolate to first mixture and cook until thickened.
Separate egg yolks.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add slowly to hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook over low heat about 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Cool and pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Chill and top with whipped cream.

title: no sugar apple pie
directions: Cook apple juice, cornstarch and spices until thick, stirring constantly.
Add salt and stir.
Add apples and mix well.
Pour in shell.
Top with second shell.
Prick holes or slits in top.
Pour melted butter over top crust.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: crispy oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Combine oil, salt, pepper, ginger, garlic and paprika in small bowl. Crush cereal in pie plate.
Dip chicken in oil mixture, then roll in cereal crumbs to coat.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Stir ingredients together. Stir in just enough salad dressing to stick the bread together.

title: short ribs in sherry
directions: Chop garlic and put on bottom of baking dish.
Slice onions. Place ribs in casserole; surround with vegetables and sprinkle with spices.
Pour sherry over all.
Bake in 350° oven, basting often.
Keep cover on for first 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover last half hour.
Lift meat and vegetables and thicken juice with flour and water to make gravy.
You may add to recipe as diners increase.

title: special chicken
directions: Marinate
chicken overnight in salad dressing.	Arrange in pan or
grill.
Sprinkle
Greek seasoning over chicken and add margarine.

title: pork tenderloin on rice
directions: Blend mushroom soup and milk; reserve 1/2 cup.
Stir in remaining soup mixture, rice, mushrooms (with liquid) and onion soup mix.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch ungreased baking dish.
Lightly brown tenderloin in skillet.
Arrange on top of rice mixture.
Pour reserved soup mixture over dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and bake 15 minutes.
Serves from 12 to 15.

title: granny oates sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° until middle is thick, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hill billy stir-fry
directions: Tenderize steaks overnight in 1 tablespoon of meat tenderizer and 2 tablespoons of water, turning several times.
Remove from marinade and pound to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into small pieces, about 1 x 1/4-inch.
Fry until brown.
Add onion and green pepper. Fry until done.
Add hominy and half of hominy juice and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce, your own or a commerical brand.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook in heavy saucepan over medium heat until thickens, stirring constantly.
Pour in prepared pie crust.

title: maine custard pie
directions: Warm but don't scald milk.
Separate egg and beat the white stiffly.
Beat in sugar, vanilla, salt and nutmeg.
Combine egg yolk with 3 eggs.
Stir gently and pour over beaten egg white. Beat slightly, only enough to blend.
Then add warm milk, stirring until sugar seems dissolved.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and place in preheated 475° oven and turn heat down to 425°.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: easy pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Combine pumpkin and pie spice.
Fold into pudding.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions on box; fold into pumpkin mixture.
Place into pie shell; chill well.

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Slice eggplant thinly.
Combine oil with herbs and brush both sides of eggplant.
Brown both sides until tender.
Layer 1/2 of eggplant slices, Mozzarella, Ricotta, spaghetti sauce, fennel seed and olives (in that order).
Repeat layering.
Top with remaining Mozzarella and garnish with sliced olives.
Cover and bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand 15 minutes (can be made with ground chuck in tomato sauce).
Serve 4 to 6.

title: chicken delight
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and spread into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the next 3 ingredients and lay over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix, nectar, oil, eggs and sugar together well. Pour into tube pan and cook 1 hour at 325°.
Mix powdered sugar and lemon juice together well. Pour on cake while hot.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine chili sauce, lemon juice, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce, onion and hot pepper sauce.
Mix well.
Cover and chill. Makes 1 cup.

title: peanut butter and m&m cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients according to order and mix well. Make into firm, packed balls and flatten.
Bake at 300°F for 10-12 min. or until golden brown.

title: nestle quik pie(this is rich!)
directions: Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly (this will scorch real easy).
Boil one minute; remove from heat and cool completely.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put into a casserole dish and crumble Ritz crackers on top.
Grate more cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil and de-bone chicken.
Cook noodles according to directions in the chicken broth.
Drain.
Saute garlic, onions, celery, and green pepper in butter.
Mix in remaining ingredients, including chicken and noodles.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: baked chicken with rice(scaled for 4 servings)
directions: Cut
chicken
breasts
in half and remove skin and fat. Season on
both sides with salt, pepper, garlic powder, onion powder and paprika.
Pour
a
little
oil
in	a
large
heavy skillet. Brown
chicken slowly on both sides.
Remove chicken from skillet. Add
rice	to
skillet and cook, stirring until rice is
slightly brown.
Add
bouillon,
green
peppers
and onions.
Mix well and transfer to 3 quart casserole. Top with browned chicken. Cover
and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until chicken is very tender and rice has absorbed all the broth and is well cooked.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and margarine in a medium bowl on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Spread evenly in crust. Refrigerate until chocolate is firm.

title: compote of beans microwave
directions: Arrange bacon slices in single layer in glass casserole dish. Cover with paper towel.
Cook on High 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove. Blend sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper with bacon drippings. Stir in vinegar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Cook on Reheat for 7 minutes.
Stir; continue cooking for 6 to 8 minutes, or until slightly thickened.
Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: girl scout "bags of gold"
directions: In a large pot bring soup and water to a boil; your need to get the "bags of gold" ready while soup is on.
Slice each biscuit in half.
Place a 1-inch cube of cheese in middle and make sure dough completely covers cheese.
Drop in boiling soup; cook about 10 minutes.
(Cover pot while cooking.)

title: fried okra
directions: Heat about 1 inch of cooking oil in a nonstick frying pan. Mix vegetables in large pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Toss with flour until well coated.
Drop by handful in hot oil.
Brown and drop on paper towel.

title: cheese breadsticks
directions: Spread	slices of bread with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cut
in
finger slices.
Bake in a 200° oven until very crisp.
Good as a snack or serve with tossed salad.

title: ham cheese log
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
In small mixer bowl, beat together Cheddar cheese and cream cheese until blended.
Beat in deviled ham.
Stir in olives and chill.
Shape into two 8-inch long logs.
Roll in pecans.
Let set overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix beef with salt and pepper.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
In skillet with lid, heat oil.
Add meat balls and cook, turning or shaking, until browned on all sides.

title: cream cheese bacon bars
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients except bread, blending well.
Sandwich mixture between bread slices.
Trim crusts.
Cut sandwiches in thirds.
(18 bars).

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, sugar, oil and sour cream.
Add the eggs, one at a time and beat.
Add poppy seed and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven.
Dust with sifted powdered sugar or frost as you prefer.

title: pizzeria macaroni
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; pour off fat.
Add onion, stir until tender.
Stir in sauce and all of the seasonings. Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Then mix egg, milk and beat together and pour over macaroni.
Mix well.
Pour macaroni mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan; add sauce with meat and spices over macaroni. Over top put shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 1/2 hour and let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: hummingbird nectar
directions: Dissolve sugar in water either on the stove or hot tap.
Fill feeders and sit back and enjoy.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Place butter in 9 x 12-inch baking dish to melt in oven at 350°.
In bowl, mix potatoes, sugar, milk, soda, flour and nutmeg. When blended, mix in eggs.
Swirl melted butter around to coat baking dish and pour in sweet potato mixture.
Place in oven and when crust begins to form around edges and on top, stir under and let crust form again.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Have sweet potatoes ready before starting.
Makes 15 servings.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In a mixing bowl mix biscuit mix, cheese, pepper and eggs. Stir until moist.
Fold in zucchini and mix well.
Use 2 tablespoons mixture for each round.
Cook in hot to medium margarine 2 to 3 minutes on each side until brown.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Cream sugar and cheese together in a small bowl.
Blend in extract.
Divide mixture in half.
Add
red
color	to
one half and green to the other half.
Knead until the consistency of
pie dough.
Form into
1/2-inch
balls;
roll
in
sugar. Press into candy molds and
remove immediately.
Makes about 2 dozen mints.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a baked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: ham and cheddar quiche
directions: Mix mayonnaise, milk, cornstarch and eggs with hand mixer. Stir in ham, cheese and pepper with wooden spoon.
Pour into pie shell and top with cooked broccoli.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve grape Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pineapple with juice and add blueberry pie filling.
Pour into mold and chill until firm, then add the following topping.

title: nutty caramel corn
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large roasting pan; set aside.
Melt butter in a large saucepan; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, without stirring (temperature will register about 250°).
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla. Pour over popped corn and nuts; stir well.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and break into pieces, if desired.
Store in an airtight container.

title: transparent pie
directions: Mix all together and
pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 items together well.
Form into ball; let chill and roll in finely chopped pecans.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add sour cream last.
Chill and serve.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix.
Use 2 or 3 tablespoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: lunch for one
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in oil.
Add spinach, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
When heated, add egg and cook until set.
Just double for two.

title: aunt vie's cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Shape into ball at serving time. Roll ball in chopped pecans. Serve with cinnamon crisp graham crackers.

title: mom's german chocolate cake
directions: Mix
package of German chocolate with hot water (melt). Mix Crisco,
sugar, flour, egg, buttermilk and soda together. Add chocolate
and water.
Fold in egg whites and add vanilla. Pour into greased cake pans and bake at 350°.

title: peach delight
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two round pans (8 or 9 1/2-inches).
Drain peaches; save sauce.
Add water and peach sauce to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box, except substitute sauce mix for water.
Pour batter into pans. Bake and cool as directed.
Mix yogurt and whipped topping; fold in peaches.
Fill cake layers with half of peach mixture.
Spoon remaining over top.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: pesto(low-fat)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender in order listed. Cover and blend on medium speed, stopping occasionally to scrape sides until almost smooth, about 2 minutes.

title: fudgy microwave brownies
directions: Grease 8-inch microwave-proof pan.
In large bowl, combine oil, granulated sugar, eggs, corn syrup and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture, beating until smooth.

title: lasagna burritos
directions: Spread 1/4 cup taco sauce thinly over bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Crumble beef into small pieces and cook until done.
Drain.
Put beef in bowl.
Stir in seasoning mix and water. Heat until thickened.
Add in refried beans.
Spread about 1/2 cup meat mixture over each noodle.
Sprinkle one end of each noodle with 1 tablespoon Cheddar cheese.
Starting with cheese end, roll up noodles carefully so filling doesn't ooze out. Arrange, seam side down, in prepared dish.
Top with remaining taco sauce.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick melted margarine and graham cracker crumbs. Spread in 9 x 12-inch glass cake pan.
Drain pineapple and spread. Mix eggs, 2 sticks margarine and powdered sugar with mixer for 15 minutes, then spread over pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Spread Cool Whip; top with cherries.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: chinese style barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a small saucepan. Simmer gently for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and cool to room temperature. Serve with chicken, barbecued ribs or pork loin.

title: low-fat cocoa chocolate cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Add powdered sugar as garnish.
Light and delicious.

title: lemon buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine together, blending well.
Add sugar gradually; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Sift flour and salt together; add alternately with buttermilk, mixing well.
Add lemon and vanilla extract; blend.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: pudding frosting
directions: Combine ingredients and beat on high speed of electric mixer until thickened, approximately 3 to 6 minutes.
Frost cake immediately and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into bottom and sides of spring-form pan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and keep in oven for an additional 30 minutes.

title: honey nut spread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat at medium speed until smooth.
Add nuts; cover and chill.
Serve with gingersnaps.

title: deep freeze biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to buttermilk; mix well.
Add to dry ingredients; mix to soft pliable dough.
Roll out, cut, place on cookie sheet and put in freezer.
When frozen, put in freezer bags, keeping frozen until ready to bake.

title: butter dips
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches, melt butter in oven.
Remove pan from oven.
Measure flour and sugar into bowl.
Add milk; stir just until dough forms, about 30 strokes.

title: slow-cooked apple butter
directions: Cook apples in crock-pot on high setting until soft, stirring occasionally.
Add 3 to 4 cups sugar (depending on sweetness of apples), 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon ground cloves. Cover; cook on high 8 to 10 hours.
Remove cover during last half of cooking.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 11 1/2 pint jars.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together.
Sugar will dissolve if mixed with hot tea. Chill.
Very good.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together and make into 1-inch balls.
