Put in refrigerator to chill.
Melt one carton almond bar and dip balls in for coating.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain liquid from vegetable mix and water chestnuts.
Mix well all ingredients together, except margarine and crackers.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Remove from oven.
Cover top with cracker crumbs. Drizzle melted margarine over top. Bake 10 minutes more or until brown.

title: chocolate syrup brownies(microwave)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add salt. Stir in chocolate syrup, flour and vanilla. Add nuts and stir to blend well.
Pour into greased and lightly floured 8-inch square microwave-safe dish.
Microwave on High power for 3 minutes.
Let rest for 3 minutes.
Microwave on High power for another 3 minutes and let rest 3 minutes. Microwave on High power for 2 minutes or until batter is set.
Let rest in pan until almost cool. Cut into squares.
Remove from pan.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry rice in fat until brown, then add water and boil until soft.
Drain.
Saute the onions in fat;
mix with tomatoes and peppers and add to the rice.
Add seasoning and place in a greased casserole.	Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta and fagioli(pasta and beans)
directions: Use Romano cheese instead of Parmesan for a more pungent taste.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Prepare pudding according to box instructions. Mix in cool whip to pudding mix. Melt frosting in microwave and set aside.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Combine cornstarch, cold water and red food coloring.
Add to first mixture.
Cook until thick, then partly cool.
Fill the 2 crusts with whole fresh berries.
Pour cooled filling over berries and chill.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Combine all the above ingredients.
Form into 1-1/2 to 2-inch balls and place on baking sheet with a rim to catch any grease run-off.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt Parkay; add peanut butter and powdered sugar; mix well. Refrigerate and cool.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Roll peanut butter mixture into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip in chocolate, lay on waxed paper to cool.
Or make miniature cups with miniature cupcake liners in miniature muffin pans.
Add small amount of chocolate in bottom, then your peanut butter ball and cover with chocolate.
Tastes like Reese's peanut butter cups.

title: apple pie deluxe
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry. Arrange apple slices in pie plate.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Place over apples and dot with butter.
Cover with Crumb Topping.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugars; add the eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add mashed bananas.
Combine flour and remaining ingredients and fold into creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Turn into greased and lightly floured loaf pan.
I like a long 4 x 13 x 1 3/4-inch pan, but the regular 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan is okay.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes for long pan or 65 to 75 minutes for short pan.

title: low-fat lamb chops with tarragon-tomato sauce
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Coat a large skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add chops and cook 4 minutes on each side or until browned.
Remove chops from skillet and drain well on paper towels.
Sprinkle chops with pepper.
Wipe skillet dry with a paper towel.

title: artichoke dip
directions: To artichoke hearts add Parmesan cheese and mayonnaise. Sprinkle on garlic powder to taste.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until top browns.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: eloise's sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil sweet potatoes and mash to measure 3 cups.
Add sugar, eggs and milk.
Put in buttered 11 x 14-inch Pyrex dish.
Cover with topping.

title: rainbow jello salad
directions: *Jell-O flavors suggested:
cherry, orange, lemon, lime and blueberry.

title: german nut macaroons
directions: Finely grind all nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add all dry ingredients and beat well.
Spoon onto cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: polish bows(chrusciki)
directions: Add sugar, salt, flour and vanilla or almond to eggs.
Knead dough until spongy, about 5 minutes.
Divide dough.
Roll out paper thin using flour so it doesn't stick.
Cut with pastry wheel into 5 x 1 1/4-inch strips.
Cut a slit about 1 1/2-inches on strip and pull strip through slit.
Deep fry to light tan color.
Cool on paper toweling.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: lasagne d'italia
directions: Cook noodles in salt water for 5 minutes; drain.
Heat oil in skillet.
Cook garlic and onions until soft; add beef and seasoning.
Cook until crumbly; add tomato paste and water. Simmer 5 minutes; set aside.
Blend cottage cheese and eggs in bowl. In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, put in thin layer of meat sauce, half the noodles and all of the cottage cheese mixture and half of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with remaining meat sauce, rest of noodles, rest of sauce and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring all ingredients except oatmeal to a rolling boil; keep stirred.
Then add oatmeal.
Drop on waxed paper.
Let set for a few minutes.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Combine mayo, curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Toss with chicken and chill several hours.
Spoon onto bed of lettuce in individual plates and sprinkle with pineapple and 1/2 of almonds.
I add roasted almonds to salad when ready to serve so they will be crunchy.

title: barbecue lemon chicken breast
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Blend well.
Simmer for about 5 to 6 minutes.
Place chicken breast on the grill and baste often.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and peel onions.
Slice cucumbers and onions 1/4 inch thick.
Cut pepper in slices.
Dissolve salt in ice water; pour over all vegetables.
Let stand 3 hours; drain.
In large kettle, mix sugar, spices and vinegar.
Add vegetables and heat to boiling.
Put hot pickles into prepared jars and seal at once. Allow pickles to ripen 1 week before using.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix
cream cheese and peppermint.
Gradually add sugar. Knead until no longer sticky.
Divide into 4 portions.
Knead in
food colors
of your choice and other flavors if desired. Shape
into 3/4-inch
balls and roll in sugar.
Flatten balls with a fork or put into special pans.
Let dry at room temperature.
Store loosely covered in the refrigerator.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In bowl, mix oats, cocoa, peanut butter and vanilla. In saucepan mix sugar, milk and margarine. Cook to boil. Pour over dry ingredients. Spoon onto waxed paper. Let cool- enjoy.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip well.
Put into pie crust.
Freeze.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches and keep 1 cup of the syrup/juice; set aside. Place peaches in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour dry cake mix over the peaches.
Pour reserved syrup/juice over top of peaches.
Stir with knife so juice will mix with cake mix.
(Do not overstir; some cake mix should still be somewhat dry.)
Dot with margarine and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (about 40 minutes).
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: cherry-berry clafouti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray pan with Pam.
Coat sides, too. Combine all ingredients, except strawberries, cherries and xxxx sugar, in a blender.
Blend at high speed 1 minute.

title: three bean chili
directions: Heat oil in large Dutch oven.
Add beef, onion and garlic; cook over high heat, stirring to break up large pieces until beef loses its pink color.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and, stirring occasionally, simmer 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender and flavors have blended.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry fruit salad
directions: Mix canned fruits, strawberries and sliced bananas.
Mix vanilla pudding and jello.
Keep mixes dry.
Sprinkle mix over fruit; stir and chill.

title: pizza appetizer
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in a 9-inch pie plate.
Pour 1/2 of sauce over cream cheese.
Add 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese and the rest of the pizza sauce to browned sausage.
Pour this in as next layer.
Add remaining cheese and seasoning as next layer.
Top with onions, green peppers (optional), olives and mushrooms.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or microwave for 12 minutes.
Serve with garlic toast.
(Dip the toast in it.)

title: salsa
directions: Drop tomatoes into hot water.
Remove skins and put into food processor.
Add peppers.
Puree peppers, onions and celery in processsor and add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook in kettle for about 2 hours, then put into jars and seal.
Makes between 8 to 10 pints.

title: banana pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
Mash bananas in small bowl.
In large bowl add flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well, but do not beat.
Add walnuts and mix.
Pour into round pan that has chimney.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until top browns.
Allow to cool before removing from pan.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ma's brown bread
directions: Mix all together and put into 2 greased one-pound coffee cans. Steam in a kettle of boiling water for 3 hours (cover cans with foil while steaming).

title: easy vegetable dip
directions: Mix together; serve with vegetables.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Layer tortillas and sauce in an oblong Pyrex dish.
Repeat. Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, cream of tartar and water.
Boil until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans and vanilla flavoring.
Stir until mixture begins to sugar.
Pour out on wax paper and separate pecans.
Let cool and store in tin.

title: cream of celery soup
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water; add to sauteed mixture.
Mix milk with flour and salt, then add to boiling mixture.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: cottage cheese refresher
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on Melba toast.

title: pralines #3
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugars and milk.
Heat and stir over low heat until dissolved.
Increase heat and cook to fine thread stage (230°).
Remove from heat; add butter and nuts.
Continue cooking until soft ball stage (236°). Cook 5 minutes.
Beat until slightly thickened.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread coconut evenly on cookie sheet. Toast, stirring occasionally, for 8 to 10 minutes, until light golden.

title: under-the-sea-salad
directions: Drain pears, reserving 3/4 cup of the syrup.
Dice pears and set aside.
Dissolve Jell-O and salt in boiling water.
Add reserved syrup and lemon juice.
Pour 1 1/4 cups into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Chill until set but not firm, about 1 hour.

title: party ham biscuits
directions: Mix oleo, mustard, onion and poppy seed.
Split each package of rolls horizontally and spread with mixture.
Layer ham and cheese on bottom of rolls.
Replace top and cut individually while in pan they came, being careful not to cut through aluminum pan. Cover with foil and refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Mix; let stand 5
minutes.
Add
butter
and
let
boil until soft ball stage (240° to
Beat and pour into wet dish towel and roll into loaf shape.
Cool and slice.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix with Cool Whip.

title: beef rolls
directions: Mix 1/2 soup, hamburger and eggs on wax paper (1/2-inch thick).
Mix the onion, butter, cheese and bell pepper.
Spread over meat mixture.
Roll like jelly roll.
Place in freezer until set.
Slice 1/2-inch thick.
Top with remainder of soup.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rice salad
directions: Cook rice. Put rice in bowl and add rest of ingredients. Mix together and let set before serving.

title: potato-fiddlehead salad
directions: Mix together vinegar, honey and celery seed.
Pour over hot drained fiddleheads and allow to stand 3 hours.
Combine potatoes, celery and onion.
(Onion may be blanched in boiling water for 1 or 2 minutes to mitigate raw taste of onion.)
Mix together mayonnaise and mustard.
Stir marinated ferns into potato mixture and blend gently.
Season to taste.
Serve at once.
Yields 6 servings.

title: potato puffs
directions: Toss flour, baking powder and salt.
Add potatoes; blend well. Beat in eggs, chopped parsley and pepper.
Fry by small spoonfuls in deep fat at 380° until golden.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain the pineapple.
Place in casserole.
Mix sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Sprinkle over the pineapple.
Cover with grated cheese.
Top with cracker crumbs and dribble melted oleo over top. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes, at 350°.

title: chicken-broccoli noodle casserole
directions: Mix chicken, cooked noodles, soup, broccoli and 3/4 bag of cheese in baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until warm, about 20 minutes.

title: congealed salad (mixed fruit)
directions: Mix all together and congeal.

title: cauliflower relish salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to boil; simmer 3 minutes. Place in container and cover.
Cool and chill overnight.
Drain to serve.

title: lemon cups
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and butter.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Add to combined egg yolks and milk.
Mix well, then fold in egg whites.
Pour into 8 greased custard cups.
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake at
for
45 minutes.
When baked each dessert will have custard on
bottom
and
sponge cake on top.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: honey glazed ham
directions: Score the ham making diamond shapes 1/2 inch deep.
Place on a rack in a well greased foil lined roasting pan.
Add water to pan.
In a small bowl combine the honey, brown sugar, cloves and mustard.
Pour over ham.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix margarine, 2/3 cup evaporated milk and cake mix together. Pour 1/2 into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: no bake rum ball cookies
directions: *If desired, substitute bourbon, brandy or Amaretto for rum.

title: peanut butter fudge cake
directions: Pour boiled mixture over sugar, flour and soda; mix well. Pour into a well-greased and floured 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool in pan.

title: little smokies snack wrap
directions: Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Cut each triangle lengthwise into fourths or fifths.
Place sausage or wieners on shortest side of each triangle.
Roll up.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm with ketchup, mustard or mustard sauce.
Makes approximately 48 appetizers.
Bake at 350°.

title: broccoli, cheese and chicken casserole
directions: Mix together cream of chicken soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Grease casserole dish.
Then layer chicken, broccoli, mayonnaise mixture and cheese; pepper to taste.
Top with crackers mixed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon steaks
directions: Combine butter and lemon juice in custard cup.
Microwave on High until butter melts.
Arrange salmon steaks in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Brush with lemon butter.
Microwave 14 to 16 minutes on Medium or until fish flakes easily.
Let stand 5 minutes, covered.

title: summer artichoke salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add Italian dressing, grated Parmesan cheese and garlic powder to taste.
Toss salad ingredients with marinade.
Chill and serve.

title: salsa
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and chop up in blender. Pour into quart jar and refrigerate.

title: salmon salad with almonds and bok choy
directions: Break the salmon into bite sized chunks and place in a large bowl.
Add bok choy, almonds and scallions.
In a small bowl, combine yogurt and cheese.
Combine with salmon mixture.
Serves 4.

title: beef brisket anna
directions: Dust beef with flour; season with salt and pepper. In large skillet, sear beef on all sides in olive oil. Add onions and saute until they begin to color.

title: acorn cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Shape into walnut-size balls.
Pinch to a point on one end to resemble an acorn.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 18 minutes.
Cool.
Melt caramels in double-boiler or microwave.
Dip top of "acorn" cookies into melted caramel and then into chopped pecans.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Shake in bag or toss in bowl until potatoes are evenly coated.
Put into baking pan.
Bake for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally, until golden brown.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: apple torte
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in greased pan, 2-inches deep, almost filling dish with apples.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar and cinnamon to taste.

title: graham fingers
directions: Line cookie sheet with graham crackers (this will take about one package)
making sure they are laying in the same direction.

title: german chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats, oleo and chocolate; cool about 20 minutes.
Add eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients, mix well.
Pour into greased (Pam) 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: press 'n bake cream cheese crust
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter; blend well.
Stir in flour. Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Remove dough from refrigerator and press into bottom and up sides of ungreased 9-inch pie pan.

title: cruditite dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a small bowl. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: best ever strawberry pie
directions: Stir, boil and let thicken the Jell-O, cornstarch, sugar and water.
Add strawberries.
Do not slice.
Bake crust.
Sprinkle a little sugar on crust before adding filling.
Add filling and top with Cool Whip.

title: easy torte
directions: Place pie filling in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with dry cake mix.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
(Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.)

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Slice strawberries and sprinkle with 1 cup of sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Heat oven to 450°.
Grease round layer pan, 8 x 1 1/2-inches.
Measure flour, 2 tablespoons of sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Cut in shortening thoroughly until mixture looks like meal.
Stir in milk just until blended. Put into pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Split shortcake while warm. Spread with butter. Fill and top with berries.
Serve warm with cream.

title: molasses popcorn balls
directions: Combine molasses, water, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Cook slowly without stirring until small quantity dropped in water forms threads.
Remove from heat.
Add butter; stir only enough to mix. Pour over popcorn, stirring constantly.
Shape into balls and be quick about it.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, sugar, cocoa, oil, milk and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle over flour mixture.
Pour boiling water over entire batter.
Bake 45 minutes.
Makes 9 servings.

title: honey-mustard baked chicken
directions: Place chicken parts in a large shallow baking pan. In saucepan, melt butter; stir in remaining ingredients and heat through. Brush glaze over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until chicken is golden brown. Baste chicken frequently with sauce while baking. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken flavored rice
directions: In medium size saucepan, mix all ingredients. Bring to a boil. Stir. Cover and cook on low heat for 20 minutes. If too dry, add a little more chicken broth until desired consistency.

title: hawaiian pudding
directions: Mix wafer crumbs with margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bananas onto wafer crumbs.
Mix milk with lemon juice; pour over layered bananas.
Next, layer crushed pineapple.
Spread whipped topping over pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut over whipped topping.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over coconut.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Melt into medium saucepan the butter.
Remove from heat.
Add all other ingredients and mix with electric mixer until well blended.
Perforate cake with fork, pour on and spread icing.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.
Put into pie shell.
Chill before serving.

title: my broccoli cheese soup
directions: Simmer broccoli in broth for 15 minutes.

Fry onion in butter until tender. Add flour and stir. This will be lumpy. Slowly add milk. Cook this until thick. Add broccoli and broth, then add cheese and stir. Do not boil. Stir until cheese is melted.

title: candy cane popcorn
directions: Mix popcorn, marshmallows and gumdrops in a large mixing bowl. Melt butter in heavy saucepan and add sugar and corn syrup. Bring to a boil, stirring, and simmer 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Pour over popcorn mixture, mixing well.
Let stand 2 minutes to cool.
With hands dampened in cool water, shape into balls, candy cane, wreaths or as desired.

title: snickers candy
directions: Spread into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: couvillion (fish)
directions: Saute onions, celery, green pepper, green onion tops and garlic.
Add tomatoes, seasonings and water.
Use cornstarch to thicken mixture.
Add wine and cook about 30 minutes.
Pour over fish fillets in a shallow baking dish.
Bake about 20 minutes. Serve over rice with salad.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage. Mix sugar and mayonnaise, then dissolve in mustard. Stir in vinegar and pour over cabbage. Salt and pepper to taste. Chill before serving.

title: toffee bar cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar and flour in large mixer bowl, on low speed, until thoroughly combined.
Cut butter into 8 pieces; cut into sugar-flour mixture with a pastry blender, until mixture is size of small peas and uniformly mixed.
Transfer 1 cup of mixture to medium bowl to use as topping.
Add milk, egg, vanilla and baking soda to remaining crumb mixture.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.
Transfer to prepared pan.
Coarsely mince candy bars; add to reserved crumbs, along with pecans.
Sprinkle evenly over cake.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 35 minutes.
Place pan on wire rack; cool completely.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and coconut.
Put in a cold oven.
Heat to 325° and bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in baked pie shell.
(Can be frozen.)
(Can use graham cracker crust.)

title: dolmeh-ye barg-e mo i(persian stuffed grape leaves)
directions: Cook split peas in boiling water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Cook rice in lightly salted water by boiling 15 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Saute onion in butter.
Add scallions and cook a few minutes more.
Mix together rice, peas, onion, scallions, eggs, currants and seasonings in a large bowl.
Drain and rinse the grape leaves and spread out flat. Put about 1 tablespoon (alter amount according to size of leaf) of rice mixture on each leaf.
Fold edges over and roll up.
Line bottom of pot with unused leaves.
Arrange stuffed ones seam side down in pot.
Mix together lemon juice or vinegar, sugar and water and pour over leaves.
Cover and simmer over low heat until tender, approximately 30 minutes (or bake 30 minutes at 350° or pressure cook on high 25 minutes).
Serves 6 to 8 as main dish, more as appetizer.

title: garden salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower in bite-size pieces.
Combine all ingredients as much as you desire.
Pour the Italian dressing over veggies.
Marinate 4 to 5 hours.

title: williamsburg souffle
directions: Trim crusts off bread, then cut in bite-size pieces.
Arrange in well buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Heat butter in skillet and saute mushrooms and onion about 5 minutes.
Spoon evenly over bread cubes.
Top with ham.
Combine cheese with flour and sprinkle over ham.
Beat eggs with mustard, half and half, garlic salt and salt to taste.
Pour into dish.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour or until puffed and lightly browned.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: dill crisps
directions: Slice pickles, crosswise into rings.
Add sugar and garlic. Store in refrigerator for a minimum of 24 hours before serving.

title: easy caramel pie
directions: Place unopened can of milk in a deep pan covered with water. The can must stay covered with water at all times.
Bring to a boil and then reduce to slow boil.
Boil for 3 hours.
Remove from heat and let cool completely.
Bake pie shell ahead of time.
When filling is cool, pour into shell.
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in small amount of oil.
Add meat and brown together.
Drain oil.
Add remaining ingredients to meat mixture.
Simmer slowly; until ingredients are hot, 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: popover pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. Brown beef with onion in large skillet, breaking up with a spoon as it cooks.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in sauce mix, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon into prepared pan and top with slices of cheese.
Place in oven to keep hot.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Blend together until smooth.
Add pecans and serve with fresh fruit.

title: jan stauffer's hominy casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Leave some drippings (2 tablespoons).
Add flour, tomatoes and seasonings. Stir. Add hominy.
Pour in a greased casserole. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chopped meat in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soups and sour cream; spread on top of meat.
Melt margarine in boiling broth.
Sprinkle dry cornbread stuffing on top of soups and sour cream.
Pour boiling broth and oleo over cornbread stuffing.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, about 30 minutes.

title: easter eggs
directions: Melt butter and blend in sugar.
Add coconut and stir well. Blend flavoring and milk into mixture.
Add cherries and nuts. Cover with wax paper and refrigerate 4 days.
Remove from refrigerator.
Let soften enough to handle well.
Shape mixture into eggs of desired size.
Place eggs on cookie sheet and return to refrigerator until crusted.

title: lemon raspberry ribbon pie
directions: In small saucepan, combine raspberries and cornstarch; cook and stir until thickened and clear.
Cool 10 minutes.
Chill thoroughly, about 20 minutes.
In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand, ReaLemon brand and food coloring, if desired.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread 1/3 lemon mixture into prepared pastry shell; top with raspberry mixture then remaining lemon mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.
Preparation time:
1 hour.
Total time:
3 hours.

title: crisp summer pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers 1/4-inch thick and put in a 2-quart jar.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and pour over the cucumbers.
Put in refrigerator.
Let set several days before eating.
Will last and keep for several months.

title: excellent egg salad
directions: Thoroughly blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and seasonings. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Makes 3 cups.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well with electric mixer.
Refrigerate.
Serve with cut up vegetables.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Cook sesame seed in water until nearly absorbed.
Add brown sugar, butter, flour, salt and egg, in that order.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, 2 of the eggs, margarine and chopped pecans together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan; then mix the powdered sugar, eggs, cream cheese and vanilla.
Pour over the crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle lightly with powdered sugar.
Cut into small pieces.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add ingredients in layers in order given.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Press lightly with spatula while hot.
Let cool in pan and cut into squares or bars. Makes 24 squares.

title: low-fat zucchini bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together. Add the zucchini.
Sift the remaining ingredients.
Add wet mixture to dry ingredients. Mix well.
(If desired, add 1/2 cup nuts or raisins.)
Grease two 8-inch loaf pans. Bake 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: macaroni-beef casserole
directions: Separate ground beef into one-inch chunks in frying pan.
Add onion and green peppers.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned.
Pour off grease and season meat mixture with salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, sauce, corn and cooked macaroni. Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°, stirring twice during baking.

title: brenna's nutty fingers
directions: Blend sugar and margarine until creamy.
Add flour, vanilla and ground pecans.
Shape dough into fingers.
Bake in a slow oven of 325° for about 20 minutes. Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix sugar and pineapple and let stand.
Beat eggs and mix with milk.
Combine the two mixtures.
Line bottom of a greased pan with bread cubes.
Pour mixture over cubes.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done (when knife inserted comes out clean).
Do not cover.
Serves 8.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Mix flour and seasonings in bowl. Put shortening in 9x13 dish, and put into oven to melt. Roll chicken in flour mixture to coat thoroughly. Place chicken, skin side down in single layer in hot shortening. Bake 30 min. Turn skin side up and bake another 30 min. or until chicken is tender. 4 servings. I always had trouble skillet frying chicken; the outside would be golden brown and the inside would still be pink. with this recipe it seems to come out just right.

title: rotel casserole
directions: Drain Ro-Tel.
Use juice with water to cook rice.
Brown meat, then drain off fat.
Cook Ro-Tel and tomato sauce in ground beef. Add 1 cup cheese and simmer until cheese is melted.
Mix in rice. Pour into casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted on top.

title: crunchy cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower into bite size bits.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Toss gently.
Stir together remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables, tossing well.
Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and shake well before pouring over salad.

title: cherry tomatoes(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Fry bacon crisp; crumble.
Add green onions and mayonnaise. Mix well.
Scoop seeds from tomatoes; let drain.
Stuff with mixture and refrigerate.
May be prepared ahead of time.

title: cappuccino
directions: Place milk in small saucepan, placing mixture over low heat. Stir constantly until milk is hot.
Remove.
Place egg in blender; process at high 10 seconds.
Slowly add hot milk and sugar.
Blend an additional 30 seconds.
Pour 3/4 cup hot coffee in 6 mugs. Pour in milk and mix.
Top each with chocolate shavings and add a cinnamon stick.
Great with rich dessert.

title: "butterhorn" rolls
directions: Melt margarine.
Add salt and sugar.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm milk and add to mixture.
Add eggs and the rest of the milk.
Stir in 2 cups flour.
Add 2 more cups flour until well mixed.
Mixture will be sticky.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Divide dough and roll into pie shape.
Cut and roll into crescent shape.
Raise 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Brush with butter.

title: petit quiche
directions: Cream butter and cheese together.
Blend in flour with pastry blender.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour baked chicken
directions: Melt butter; add onions, green peppers and carrots. Cook 5 minutes, then add ketchup, pineapple juice, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce, salt, pepper and ginger. Cook until mixture reaches boiling state; stir constantly. Add pineapple chunks; remove from heat. Pour mixture over chicken pieces.
Bake in covered dish at 400° for 45 minutes. Remove cover; continue baking, uncovered, for additional 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all together with mixer.
Cook in greased Bundt pan for 1 hour or until done at 325°.

title: cajun shrimp stew
directions: Heat butter, margarine or vegetable oil in large soup pot. Saute onions and garlic over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add carrots, potatoes, stock or water, orange juice and toasted coriander (toast coriander seed in a 400° oven in a shallow pan for 2 minutes).
Simmer 30 minutes until carrots and potatoes are soft. Remove from heat.
When cool, transfer vegetable mixture to blender or food processor.
Puree mixture in blender or food processor until smooth and return to soup pot.
Add whipping cream, half and half or milk and coriander leaves.
Heat, but do not boil.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pineapple-apple dessert
directions: Cook pineapple with juice, sugar, flour and oleo over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick (about 5 minutes).
Set aside to cool.
Peel and chop apples finely and add to cooked pineapple mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch or similar size dish.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with chopped nuts. Refrigerate a couple hours or overnight.
If you want more color in dessert, don't peel apples.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat.
Add soda and vanilla, gradually pouring over popcorn.
Mix well.
Bake at 250° one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store tightly covered.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: In medium bowl,
stir together flour, baking powder and salt. Combine milk, egg and zucchini.
Add to dry ingredients and mix just
until moistened.
Drop from tablespoon into deep Crisco heated to 375°.
Fry a few at a time until golden, 3 to 4 minutes. Drain
on
paper towel.
Makes 24 fritters.
Serve with Cheese Sauce.

title: butterscotch walnut candy
directions: Mix pudding and sugar together.
Slowly pour in evaporated milk.
Add oleo; stir constantly.
Bring to a full boil.
Lower heat; cook and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add walnuts; beat until it thickens slightly.
Drop by teaspoons onto aluminum foil.
Let cool.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: baked potato chips
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Spread 1 tablespoon each of olive oil on 2 cookie sheets, then put them into oven to preheat for 10 minutes. Slice the potatoes lengthwise, thin. Place slices on the hot cookie sheets. Don't overlap potatoes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake chips for 10 minutes; rotate baking sheets in oven and bake another 10 minutes. Flip each chip, then bake another 5 minutes or until golden brown. Remove chips to a paper towel to cool. These chips are great with any dip.

title: zesty chili pasta
directions: In roasting pan, place onions and Serrano chili peppers. Cover; cook for 8 to 10 minutes over high heat, or until skin chars on chilies.
Stir in tomatoes and chili.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Prepare vermicelli according to package directions.
Serve sauce over vermicelli.
Sprinkle with pumpkin seeds and cilantro.

title: grandma jones' pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Separate eggs and beat whites with 6 tablespoons of sugar, added gradually.
Put in refrigerator. Cream butter and rest of sugar; then add egg yolks and blend on medium speed.
Set on lowest speed and add flour and evaporated milk alternately; add flavorings.
Then quickly fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly mix sugar, applesauce, oil, egg whites, and milk.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, and nutmeg; sift well.
Add sugar mixture to flour mixture and mix well.
Put in loaf pan (9x5 inches) which has been greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick tester is clean.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a large saucepan, bring butter, brown sugar and Karo syrup to a low boil.
Add baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Continue on low boil for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour this over popcorn and stir in.
(A large roasting pan works well for mixing this.)

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel and thinly slice the potatoes.
Cook until just tender. Drain and set aside.
In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp; remove and drain.
Cook onion in bacon drippings until golden brown.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook until bubbly, stirring constantly, over low heat.
Remove from heat; stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Crumble bacon.
Carefully stir bacon and potatoes into hot mixture.
Heat thoroughly and serve while hot.

title: nutty fingers(grandma's)
directions: Mix together soft butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in flour and chopped pecans.
Take small spoonfuls of dough and form into finger length pieces with hand.
Place on ungreased pan and bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until edges of cookies are lightly brown.
Let cool and roll in additional powdered sugar.

title: orange juice delight
directions: Put everything in a blender and mix well.

title: roman beans soup
directions: *Recipe for 1/2 a bag.

title: barbecue chicken in a sack
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken and heat.
Salt and flour chicken pieces.
Then dip in sauce that has been heated.
When saturated, place in a well-greased paper grocery bag.
Twist bag closed.
Place on broiler pan.
Cook 15 minutes at 450°, then lower to 250° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Combine butter, sugar and water , bring to a boil and simmer for 1 minute.
Put 1 tablespoon mixture in each compartment of a 24 hole greased muffin tin.
Evenly distribute nuts in tin. Unroll crescent dough into 3 rectangles.
Sprinkle with raisins. Roll each rectangle up like jelly roll.
Cut each into 8 parts, cut side down.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender for about 15 seconds. Add 1 1/2 cups pecans. Blend 5 more seconds. Pour into pie shell. Top with whole half pecans. Bake 35 minutes at 400°.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and water.
Coat pork and fry until done, but not hard.
Drain and pour off grease.
Saute vegetables.
Combine pineapple juice, cornstarch, sugar, soya sauce, vinegar and catsup to make 2 cups.
Pour in skillet to thicken to bubbly.
Add pineapple, cherries and pork.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Combine egg white and all other ingredients in mixing bowl. Stir until nuts are coated.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 4 cups.

title: egg souffle
directions: Brown and drain sausage and bacon.
Butter a 9 x 12-inch pan. Sprinkle 1 cup cheese on bottom.
Break eggs, then break yolks; don't stir.
Distribute evenly.
Add sausage and bacon evenly. Pour whipping cream over mixture, then add remaining cheese. Cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: overnight breakfast
directions: Mix together bread, ham and cheese; place in a 9 x 11-inch greased pan.

title: potato pierogi
directions: Chop onions and saute in butter.
Set aside.
Cook bow ties according to package.
Set aside.
Boil and mash potatoes.
Add Velveeta cheese which you have sliced.
Mix well.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Begin with 1/2 onion mixture on bottom of pan.
Add 1/2 bow ties as the next layer, then 1/2 of the potatoes.
Repeat ending with potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: iona's sunday cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package; bake 20 minutes on a large cookie sheet.
Cool.
Combine pudding mix, milk and cream cheese; beat until thick and well blended; spread on cooled cake. Layer well-drained crushed pineapple on pudding mixture.
Top with thinly sliced bananas.
Cover bananas with Cool Whip.
Spoon pie filling over Cool Whip and sprinkle chopped walnuts on top. Refrigerate 3 hours.
Best if served same day.

title: quick mexican camping casserole
directions: In medium skillet, combine ground beef and onion.
Cook until beef is brown.
Drain grease.
In bottom of an oblong ungreased dish, arrange corn chips.
Layer with beef and onion mixture, beans, lettuce and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and add salsa before serving.

title: monti's roman bread
directions: Add sugar and yeast to lukewarm water; stir to dissolve yeast. Add flour, 2 teaspoons salt and onion.
Knead until smooth. Place dough in an oiled bowl and let rise until doubled in size. Punch dough down.
Flatten the dough on oiled cookie sheet to about one inch thick.
Oil the top of the dough.
Let it rise until doubled in size.
Sprinkle with salt and dried rosemary. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin bread(low cholesterol)
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add baking powder, soda, salt and spices;
sift twice.
Add nuts and fruit (which have been chopped) to flour mixture until well coated.
Measure sugar and oil in another bowl; cream well.
Add egg whites a little at a time.
Add pumpkin.
Add flour mixture alternately with water.
Batter will be thin.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: holiday yams
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Blend well.
Stir in juice, butter and salt.
Simmer over low heat until slightly thickened. Place potatoes in casserole.
Pour sauce over and heat until hot.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Mix in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan with fork the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Make three holes, one for vanilla, one for vinegar and one for oil.
Over all pour 2 cups cold water. Mix with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
When it comes out clean, cake is done.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cream puffs
directions: In saucepan, heat water, butter and salt to a full rolling boil.
Reduce heat and stir in flour, stirring vigorously, until mixture leaves sides of pan in a ball.
Remove from heat and beat in eggs one at a time, beating until mixture is smooth.
Drop with mixing spoon about three inches apart on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and continue baking 25 minutes.
Puffs are done when double in size, brown and firm to the touch.
Remove from oven; cut the side of each with a sharp knife.
Put back in turned off oven for 10 minutes.
Cool. Split top and fill with vanilla filling.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Blend cheese and sugar mixtures into the whipped cream.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Pour blueberry pie filling on top of cheese mixture. Refrigerate several hours.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese; stir in vegetable mixture.
Separate crescent rolls into triangles; place in ungreased quiche pan or 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Press dough over bottom and sides of pan to form crust.

title: baked pork chops and gravy
directions: Wash pork chops; lay in a bread pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place onion slices on each pork chop.
Place in a preheated 400° oven and bake about 1 hour.
Take pork chops out of oven and put in a large bowl.
Pour onions and pork chops drippings into a skillet.
Add a little more oil, if needed.
Add flour and brown.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over pork chops and serve.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs, then milk and blend well.
Stir
in
dry	ingredients
and
blend.
Add oatmeal, nuts, raisins, chocolate chips and vanilla; mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls
onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: italian rice casserole
directions: Boil rice; set aside.
Brown cut-up sausage, onion, garlic, mushrooms and saffron in skillet.
Then add rice, all at one time. Add broth, a cup at a time, until it has been absorbed by the rice. Keep sprinkling on cheese until you use the whole can.
Then put in baking dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: spinach squares
directions: Beat together first five ingredients.
Add cheese and spinach. Stir.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pickle slices
directions: Drain pickle slices.
Add sugar and roll around in jar until sugar is dissolved.
Add Tabasco and salt; refrigerate.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake as directed. Let cool.
Punch holes in cake with fork.
Pour on Eagle Brand milk.
Pour topping.
Cover and let set overnight,
refrigerated.
Top with Cool Whip and Heath bars.

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Heat 2 to 3 inches of Crisco oil in deep fryer or large saucepan to 375°.

title: fish cakes (main dish or hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Remove skin and bones from fish.
Mix with equal quantity of mashed potatoes.
Add salt, pepper and parsley and a little butter.
Add 1/2 beaten egg.
Shape mixture into cakes and dip in egg and then breadcrumbs.
Fry in oil until golden brown.
Serve with ketchup.

title: creamy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat with electric mixer the butter, sugars, egg and vanilla. Mix with spoon flour, baking soda and salt. Add chocolate chips. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: creamy bleu cheese dip
directions: Mix together and serve with veggies.

title: holiday date pudding
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, put brown sugar and water and let come to a boil.
Mix sugar, flour, milk, baking powder, salt and vanilla, then add dates and nuts.
The trick is to add pudding to hot syrup without disturbing syrup much.
Spoon evenly into syrup.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
May need to adjust time if oven is not accurate.

title: oriental flank steak
directions: Place steak in large shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour over steak; cover and marinate in refrigerator 8 hours, turning steak occasionally.
Drain steak, reserving marinade.
Grill over hot coals 10 minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness, basting often with marinade.
To serve, slice across grain into thin slices.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken
in
lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with cheese.
Combine soup and water stirring well. Spoon sauce
over
chicken
evenly
and sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle butter
over
the crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing mix using package directions.
Combine ground beef with evaporated milk in bowl; mix well.
Shape into 5 (6-inch) patties on waxed paper.
Spoon 1/4 cup stuffing into center of each patty.
Fold edges of patties over to enclose filling; seal edges.
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine catsup, soup and Worcestershire sauce in saucepan.
Heat to the boiling point.
Pour over patties.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done to taste.
Yield:
5 servings.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Mix Butter Buds well with 4 ounces water.
Mix chicken bouillon with 8 cups water.
Simmer ingredients 2 1/2 hours.
Add 1 pound Velveeta cheese and simmer 1/2 hour more.
Add 3 tablespoons cornstarch with 1/2 cup water.
Simmer until thickened.

title: melon and grape salad
directions: Toss fruit with 1 tablespoon of lime juice and refrigerate, covered.
When ready to serve, pour off any liquid, drying out the serving bowl.
Whisk together the remaining lime juice, honey and mustard. Toss with fruit.
Serves 6.

title: salmon dip
directions: Mix. Let it cool in fridge. Crush 1 cup pecans and roll on and ball until firm.

title: russian salad
directions: Mix water and Jell-O together until dissolved over medium heat.
Add cream cheese and marshmallows until dissolved.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour in dish and chill until firm.

title: icing
directions: Beat sugar, egg white and lemon juice until well blended.

title: peanut clusters
directions: In top of double boiler melt chocolates together.
When smooth, add peanuts.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: low calorie salmon spread
directions: Place cottage cheese in the bowl of a food processor and process until creamy.
Transfer to a medium-size bowl and mash in the olive oil, salmon and yogurt.
Fold in the green pepper and onion.
Add the dill weed, Worcestershire and Tabasco and stir. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: date bars
directions: Mix in order.
Bake in ungreased pan at 350° for 35 minutes. Cut into squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar while still warm.

title: crunchy bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch muffin cups.

title: ice cream bars
directions: Mix together the crackers and oleo.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake the mixture for 5 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Split English muffins.
Blend all.
Spread ingredients on each half.

Put in freezer container in layers, separated with tinfoil. When ready to use, cut frozen English muffins in 6 small wedges. Place in toaster oven or oven to broil until lite brown and crisp. Serve hot.
Delicious.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs and butter; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan or 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
In small bowl, toss 1/2 cup chips with flour to coat.
Stir in cheese mixture.

title: angel thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix ingredients into stiff mixture. Make into 1-inch balls, then dip into egg whites and roll in nuts. Place on cookie sheet. Make thumbprints and fill in with jelly. Bake until done.

title: dried apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, jam, raisins and nuts and apples.
Sift flour, spices and salt together, mixing all together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix fruit in any amount desired.
Toss with salad greens. Just before serving, toss with French dressing or pass dressing around when serving.

title: frozen lemon cake
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until thick as cream.
Cool. Gently mix in stiffly beaten egg whites and whipped cream.
Use crumbs for top and bottom.

title: selene's brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions and pour into greased 9x13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over batter.
Bake as directed on package, removing from oven 3 minutes earlier than directed or as soon as sides start to pull away from pan.

title: pizza doh
directions: Mix, let rise until double.
Spread on pizza pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: pork chops and chilies casserole
directions: In a skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Brown pork chops on both sides. Remove and set aside.
In the same skillet, saute the onion, chilies and celery until onion is tender. Stir in rice. Saute until lightly browned. Add soup, water and soy sauce. Blend well.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole. Top with pork chops.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until rice is tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini according to directions on package.
(Do not overcook.)
Drain and add to the 2 packages of Zesty Italian salad dressing mix.

title: beet jelly
directions: Follow directions on Sure-Jell package, then add sugar and Kool-Aid together. Fill jars and seal.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple chunks, juice, sugar, flour and cheese.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Melt butter; mix with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
(Makes 4 to 6 servings.)

title: pineapple-cheese salad
directions: Mix above ingredients; pour into 9x13 pyrex; chill until firm.

title: ham or bacon onion stuffing
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, place chopped stems and onion. Cover.
Microwave on High (10) for 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes. To hot mixture, add cream cheese, mashing and mixing well. Stir in crumbs and ham or bacon.

title: toasty pecan pie
directions: Combine all but nuts and mix well.
Add pecans and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone.
Dip tortillas in warm chicken broth.
Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole and line with tortillas (overlapping).
Layer chicken, onion, pepper, soups and cheese.
Pour tomatoes over all.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Stir in mashed bananas, then add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour 8 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Will freeze well.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Place first 7 ingredients into a bowl in order given.
Beat until smooth.
Place 1/3 of batter into a greased tube pan. Arrange apple slices on top of batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Repeat two more times.
(Batter, apples, cinnamon and sugar.)
Bake in a 325° oven for about 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.

title: ann's twice-baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and cover with margarine.
Bake on cookie sheet until tender with fork.
Remove potatoes and cut oval shape on bottom of each one.
Scoop out all potatoes into bowl, scraping out as much as possible.
Add onions, celery, 1 to 1 1/2 sticks margarine, salt and pepper to potato mixture.
Combine well and pile mixture into potato shells.
Bake again on cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots and onion together in boiling salted water until very tender, 30 to 45 minutes.
Drain and mash, then transfer to an electric mixer bowl.
Using the mixer, blend in butter, eggs, milk and cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce; season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Top should be lightly browned and the casserole firmly set in center.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream cheese, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla with mixer 5 minutes.
Pour over batter and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: crab mold
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in cold water.
Mix with soup and cool. Cream the cheese and mayonnaise.
Rinse and break apart crab.

title: chicken and salsa
directions: Place chicken breast in baking dish. Pour salsa over the chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour or until chicken done. Add cheese the last 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin loaves
directions: Heat oven to
Grease
well
3 (7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/4-inch) loaf pans.

title: chunky chippers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt together in bowl.
Beat sugar, shortening, peanut butter, eggs, vanilla and water in bowl until creamy.
Add flour mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake about 12 to 14 minutes or until firm to touch.
Let cool and enjoy!

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix celery, onion and chestnuts in a greased 9 x 16-inch pan. Add turkey, mayonnaise and soup.
Pour over turkey.
Mix stuffing with water and butter; put on top of soup mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper; drain.
In saucepan combine both soups, 1 can water, cheese and 2 teaspoons garlic salt; simmer over low heat until cheese is melted.
Cook spaghetti 6 to 8 minutes, drain and rinse.
Combine all mixtures into 3-quart casserole dish and mix well.
Top with additional cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding (small box) and pineapple, undrained.
Add rest of ingredients well and chill.

title: cherry's sinful salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water, stir until dissolved.
Cool. Add bananas, pecans and strawberries.
Stir until combined. Divide in half.
Pour half in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Keep remaining at room temperature and spread sour cream over set jello.
Top with the rest of jello mix and strawberries.

title: beef tacos
directions: Brown meat until crumbly; add other ingredients.
Blend well and heat through.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, lemon juice, pineapple juice, salt and butter in double boiler.
Cook over hot water until thick. Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Gently stir in fruits, marshmallows and nuts.
Chill 24 hours.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Stir and then melt 1/4 cup margarine and add to Potato Buds mixture and stir well.
Beat 1 egg in large bowl and add 1 tablespoon water.
Dip chicken into egg mixture and then roll in Potato Buds mixture to coat chicken.
Coats about 3 pounds of chicken.
Bake in buttered baking dish for 50 to 60 minutes until golden brown.

title: back home's cornbread salad
directions: In a large bowl, break up corn muffins.
Add mayonnaise, green pepper, onion and celery.
Fold in tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle bacon over top of salad, if desired. Refrigerate.
Serves 6.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients; set aside.
Have apples sliced thin. Beat eggs, sugar, fruit juice, vanilla, baking powder, flour and oil.
Put in tube pan batter first, then sliced apples, then cinnamon mixture.
Do this 2 or 3 times.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over chops, then cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: grandma's french toast
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Soak bread slices in mixture 10 minutes until moisture has been absorbed.

title: orange ginger ale salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over lemon juice in a glass measuring cup to soften.
Stir over hot water until dissolved.
Stir into sugar, salt, orange juice and ginger ale.
Refrigerate, stirring often, until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in orange sections and nuts.
Pour into a 1 1/4-quart ring mold or glass bowl. Refrigerate until firm.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Add mashed potatoes and milk; small amount until desired consistency.
Spread in an 8 x 8 or round Pyrex.
Place slices of Velveeta cheese on top and bake in 350° oven until cheese browns, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Check in 10 minutes.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Pour over melted butter.
Add peaches.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: meal in a dish
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Season with salt and pepper as you fill dish with the following, in order:
a layer of raw, sliced potatoes, a layer of raw rice, a layer of raw onions, a layer of raw ground beef (crumbled up).
Cover all with about a pint of canned tomatoes.
Bake at 375° for about 1 1/2 hours, or until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients together.
Roll in ball and coat in paprika.

title: sausage twirls
directions: Combine biscuit mix, milk, and butter in a large bowl until blended. Refrigerate dough for 30 minutes. Divide refrigerated dough into 2 portions and roll out each portion on wax paper to 1/8 inch thick rectangles, each about 10x7-inch. Spread half the uncooked sausage over dough, top sausage with peppers and onions, if desired. Roll lengthwise into a log. Repeat process with remaining ingredients. Place both logs, wrapped, in freezer until hard enough to cut easily, about 1 hour. Preheat oven to 400° F. Cut each log into 24 thin slices and place on non-stick baking sheets. Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown. Remove twirls from oven and serve warm.

title: family living special wedding cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, salt and vanilla together.
Add flour and pecans.
Mix well.
Roll into walnut sized balls.
Bake on cookie sheet for about 1 hour at 275°.
Remove from oven; roll into confectioners sugar.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar again.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; blend thoroughly.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in a greased or floured 9 x 13 pan.
When done top with the following mixture.

title: lime ice
directions: Mix contents in a 2-quart pitcher with water.
Pour into two ice cube trays.
Freeze.
Remove 3 or 4 cubes into a cup or bowl and chop with fork.

title: barbecued corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Place in casserole; top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain then add soup.
Pour into a greased 8 inch square pan.
Top with tater tots.
Bake for 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy barbecue beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole. Cover.
Microwave at power level High for 20 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy short cookies
directions: Mix together and roll in small balls; press with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Can make 1/2 recipe.

title: rita's venison steak
directions: Brown steak.
Add some water and simmer until almost tender. Add onion and soup and simmer until tender.
Can also add green pepper if desired.

title: congealed waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add lemon juice and let cool. Stir in crushed pineapple, celery, apples and pecans.
Stir in mayonnaise and then Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until set.

title: sesame beef strips
directions: Slice beef thinly across the grain.
In shallow bowl, mix sesame seed, flour and spices.
Dip beef strips into broth, then toss in flour mixture.
Set aside.
Heat oil in wok or nonstick skillet until hot.
Add onion and pepper; saute for 2 minutes. Add mushrooms; continue cooking 1 minute longer.
Add beef.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Grease large (10 x 14-inch) roaster pan.
This is better than a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Clean the chiles and remove all seeds, dry on paper towels.
Lay them side by side to cover the bottom of the roaster.
Distribute the whole pound of Cheddar cheese over the top of the chiles.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over the Cheddar and chiles.
Top all with the pound of Jack cheese and bake in a 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes, or until golden brown. Serve plain or with salsa.

title: hot cheese goodies
directions: Mix enough milk with eggs to make a creamy mixture (1/4 cup). Take 3 slices bread; dip one in mixture and place between 2 plain slices.
Cut 3 layers into 6 small squares.
Dip each square in melted butter.
Roll in Parmesan cheese.
Freeze on cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done; remove from bone.
In separate pan, cook noodles in 2 quarts water until tender.
Add chicken to noodles. Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Simmer on low heat until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli muffins
directions: Mix and cook in tiny muffin tins, greased and floured.
Cook at 350° until lightly browned.

title: tomato pie
directions: Combine 1 cup mayo with 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Place one layer of sliced tomatoes on pie crust.
Sprinkle with chopped onion, basil, salt and pepper to taste.
Continue to layer.
Spread mayo-cheese on top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chinese veggie salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and chopped onions.
Mix well. Combine sugar and vinegar in bowl and mix well.
Pour over veggies.
Toss to mix.
Chill overnight, stirring every once in a while.
Yield: 15 servings.

title: tuna-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as package label directs; drain.

title: cherry pie salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion until beef is brown; drain.
Spread 1/2 cup of the salsa in bottom of ungreased square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Mix remaining salsa, sour cream, soup and pimientos.
Layer half of the tortilla strips, beef mixture, soup mixture and cheese on salsa; repeat.

title: tomato soup casserole
directions: Put vegetables in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Crumble raw hamburger on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour tomato soup and 1/2 can water over all.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add soda to buttermilk; add to mixture.
Place flour in a large bowl.
Add dates, orange slices and nuts; stir to coat fruit and candy.
Add flour mixture and coconut to creamed mixture.
This makes a very stiff mixture that should be mixed by hands.
Put in a greased 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan; bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: mary's deep dish hash
directions: In frying pan, brown the meat of your choice with 3/4 of the onion; drain.
In deep baking dish, layer all ingredients, except cheese and 1/4 of onion.
On the bottom, put hash browns, next meat, then corn; top with soup.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and add cheese and 1/4 onion.
Return to oven and bake for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: matt's simple barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all except butter
in saucepan; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in butter, if desired. Serve warm.
Makes about 3 cups, enough for a large brisket.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese together.
Pour into pie plate.
Add salsa first, then add all the vegetables. Next, add the hamburg, then the Cheddar cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: black bean and tomato with rice
directions: Cook down until about 1/2 of liquid is left.
Serve over cooked rice.
Can use white, brown or wild rice.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Grease 2 large cookie sheets.
Set oven at 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat as you add sugar gradually and whites are thick.
Fold in salt and vanilla.
Then fold in chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
As soon as cookies are in oven, turn oven off and leave until morning.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Mix, roll and cut.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: beef chili
directions: Cook beef with garlic, onion, green pepper and chili powder. Add the remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until thick.
Stir occasionally.
Serve garnished with shredded cheese.

title: holiday brew to make your house smell good
directions: Simmer, uncovered, during the holidays!
Smells great!

title: polynesian ham
directions: Brown left over Ham in butter.
Add green peppers and pineapple tidbits (include juice). Cover, simmer 15 minutes.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook lasagna noodles to desired doneness. Drain and rinse with hot water.
In large saucepan, melt margarine; add mushrooms, garlic, salt and lemon juice.
Saute until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour and chicken bouillon; blend well. Add milk.
Cook over medium-high heat until mixture thickens and boils, stirring constantly.
Stir in chicken.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes before serving.

title: l and s bar-b-q
directions: Crumble ground beef into large roast pan.
Add ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir frequently.
Serves approximately 60.

title: winter fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookies as directed and bake.
Let cool.
In small bowl beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Spread mixture over cookie.
Arrange fruit as desired on cheese mixture.
May use any kind of fruit.
Strawberries and bananas are really good.

title: anaheim chili sauce
directions: Remove all seeds from pepper and chop in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in a heavy 4 gallon pot.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently for 4 to 5 hours.
Jar sauce up in hot, sterilized jars and lids.
Great for baked fish, beef or pork.

title: chicken chili
directions: Remove skin from chicken; cut meat from bones and cut meat into 1-inch cubes.
Brown in kettle with 2 tablespoons salad oil. Stir in onions, green pepper and garlic; saute until tender.
Add chili powder, salt and pepper.
Stir in tomatoes; bring to boil. Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Add kidney beans and Mexican style corn.
Cook until heated.
Cheese may be sprinkled on top of chili when serving.
Serves 4.
Use heavy kettle when cooking.

title: hazel's chocolate candy
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add cream and add margarine and vanilla. Cook over medium heat, about 20 minutes.
(Test candy and drop a few drops into a cup of cool water if ball or lump forms.)
Set off heat and add peanut butter.
If no lump forms, cook 5 to 10 minutes longer, then add peanut butter.
Pour onto buttered platter.
Chill, cut and serve.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Spray a 9 X 13-inch baking pan with Pam.
Set aside.
Soften margarine and add to sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat until combined.
Stir in syrup, then flour.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Pour on the glaze.

title: red punch
directions: Prepare according to directions on cans of fruit punch, frozen lemonade and frozen grape juice.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Put in two greased and floured 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and remove from pans.
Drizzle with Orange Glaze.

title: enchilada sauce
directions: Melt oil in large saucepan.
Add chili powder, flour, garlic salt, oregano and cumin; stir until well blended.
Gradually stir in 6 cups hot chicken broth and stir to boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook till forms soft balls in cold water add butter and vanilla.

title: johnny biette(large recipe)
directions: Saute ground meat and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put into casserole the tomatoes, corn, meat and, noodles (spaghetti) that have been coated with part of the cheese.
Slightly mix together, then top with remainder of cheeses and bake in greased bowl at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with green salad and garlic bread.

title: eggplant saute(palestinian)
directions: Saute onion and eggplant in oil.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste and allspice.
Serve over rice.
Try substituting zucchini for the eggplant.

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, heat soup and milk to boiling, stirring often. Stir in vegetables.
Return to boiling.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in cheese and heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Mix baking mix and water until dough forms.
Smooth into ball on cloth covered surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 15 times. Roll into rectangle, 15 x 9-inches. Spread with mustard. Top with remaining ingredients.
Roll up tightly, beginning at 15-inch side.
Pinch edge into roll (moisten if necessary). Wrap and refrigerate at least 30 minutes but no longer than 24 hours.
Heat oven to 400°.
Cut into 12 slices.
Place on greased and floured cookie sheet (replace filling if necessary).

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Mix yeast with warm water or milk and add other ingredients. Knead more than biscuits, but not as much as rolls.
Cut with biscuit cutter 1/4-inch thick.
Brush with butter.
Fold in half and let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: luscious orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Chill.

title: cinnamon roll cookies
directions: In a small bowl dissolve yeast in water.
In a large bowl add flour, salt and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cut in margarine.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add to flour mixture.
Next add yeast mixture and combine lightly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: oyster stew
directions: Pour 2 cans of water in oysters. Boil 3 minutes.
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper. Boil until milk comes to top.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Add Crisco.
Mix with a fork until crumbly.
Add egg, water and vinegar.
Mix well.
Form into 3 balls and chill 20 minutes.
Makes 3 pie crusts.
Will keep in refrigerator overnight, or freezes well.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and cornstarch.
Add egg yolks, buttermilk and flavor.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake until firm or brown lightly.
Top with meringue.
Bake until brown.

title: homemade hot fudge sauce
directions: In a 1 1/2 quart saucepan, melt together chocolate pieces and butter.
Gradually add the powdered sugar and evaporated milk, stirring constantly.
Bring mixture to boil; reduce heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 8 minutes.
Remove saucepan from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Let sauce stand for 10 minutes.
Store any leftover sauce in refrigerator.
To reheat, spoon desired amount in saucepan and heat over low heat, stirring constantly.

title: garlic grits
directions: Bring milk and water almost to a boil.
Add salt and grits, stirring constantly, until it thickens.
Remove from heat and beat eggs.
Add some of the hot mixture to eggs.
Stir eggs mixture into grits.
Add cheese and butter.
Stir until cheese and butter melts.
Top with cornflakes or Ritz crackers, crumbled.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: whipped cornbread
directions: Mix meal, flour, whipping cream and water.
Mix in egg.
Melt margarine; add to mixture, mixing well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan; bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then turn on broil until golden brown.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spicy sweet potato souffle
directions: Heat oven to 375°.

In bowl of electric mixer, beat mashed sweet potatoes with softened butter, light brown sugar, bourbon, cayenne pepper and ground cinnamon 2 minutes or until fluffy. Stir in light cream and 3 egg yolks.
In separate bowl, using electric mixer, beat egg whites on high speed 5 minutes or until stiff peaks form; fold into sweet potato mixture.
Pour mixture into buttered 1 1/2-quart souffle dish; sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake 45 minutes or until souffle is puffed and golden brown on top.

title: delicious breakfast cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Add the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture, alternating with the soured milk.
Pour half the batter in pan, then add half of topping mixture of nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
(Baking soda can be added to the milk.)

title: easy rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a greased casserole dish and bake for one hour in a 375° oven.
Stir once while baking to make sure butter mixes in well.

title: no fat veggies in the oven(for:  jason, john and shane)
directions: Slice potatoes (do not peel, unless want to).
Peel and quarter onions.
Wash and cut peppers and slice in rings.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven at 400°.
Mix margarine, cheese, bread crumbs and spices together.
Dip chicken in mixture; place in 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain and wash sauerkraut under cold water.
Squeeze and pull apart.
Wash again and squeeze and rinse until all of canned water is out.
Mix rest of ingredients together with sauerkraut.
Chill overnight.
Keep in glass container in refrigerator.

title: mom's peach cobbler
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 7 x 10-inch baking dish.
Cut butter and cream cheese into flour and brown sugar.
Stir in egg, vanilla and nuts.
Crumble on top of peach mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: maryland oyster stew
directions: In 4-quart pan, cook oysters with liquor over low heat until edges of oysters just begin to curl.
Add milk, margarine/butter, salt and pepper.
Heat slowly until hot.
Do not boil.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Let butter and shortening stand at room temperature, then cream oleo or butter and Crisco.
Add brown and white sugar until creamy.
Be sure batter is smooth.
Next add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla, then mix flour and other ingredients.
Add chips and nuts with spoon.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet by spoonfuls.
Use a spatula to push it off the spoon.
Bake about 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Let cool before stacking.
Makes 6 dozen. Temperature 350°.

title: mama ruth's shrimp etouffee
directions: Season raw peeled shrimp with salt, black pepper and red pepper to taste.
Melt oleo.
Add onions, celery and tomato paste. Cook until wilted.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and add to mixture.
Add shrimp and more water.
Cook over medium heat about 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: individual taco salads
directions: Heat 3-inches Crisco oil in deep fryer or heavy saucepan to 375°.
Place 1 tortilla in oil.
Let float 5 to 10 seconds.
Press center of tortilla into oil with metal ladle (tortilla will form a bowl shape).
While pressing with metal ladle, fry 1 minute longer or until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Repeat with remaining tortillas.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix and bake in 2 loaf pans for 45 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: flan
directions: Heat 3/4 cup sugar until it turns light brown on low heat. Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Coat the bottom and side of dish.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, then add 1 cup sugar slowly, while beating mixture; set aside.
In a saucepan, heat milk on medium heat with cinnamon stick until bubbly.
Take cinnamon stick out.
Pour into dish that has the caramel.
Place dish inside a bigger pan.
Pour hot tap water around the flan in the bigger pan until water is an inch deep.
Cook at 325° in oven uncovered for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco until pea size; add water.
Mix and roll into 2 pie shells.
Bake until very light brown at 350°.

title: lemon torte
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add flour and nuts.
