Spread in
a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter very slowly in heavy saucepan. Meanwhile, heat the water to boiling.
When chocolate and butter have melted, add water.
Stir well.

title: old fashioned vinegar pie
directions: Combine the six ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: baked ham loaf
directions: Combine meat with cracker crumbs, milk and eggs.
Shape into loaf.
Blend mustard, sugar and pineapple juice and bring to a boil.
Pour over ham loaf and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: out of this world salad
directions: Put jello and marshmallows
in large mixing bowl.
Pour the boiling water over	these
and stir until marshmallows are partly melted.
Add crushed
pineapple;
mix
well.
Put	in refrigerator
until
almost
jelled.
Remove;
add
chopped pecans, cottage cheese and cherries cut in small pieces.
Mix. Fold in Cool Whip last.
Keep refrigerated until firm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease and lightly flour two 5 x 9 loaf pans. In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until frothy. Beat in sugar. Add oil and vanilla. Beat until thick and lemon colored. Add loosely packed grated zucchini.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Combine in saucepan and cook to soft ball stage (238°).
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat until mixture loses it gloss.
Then add 1/2 cup broken pecans or walnuts.
Pour into pan.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Toss together the bread crumbs and crumbled corn bread. Add the poultry seasoning. Add sage to taste. Add the salt and pepper. Cook the onions in the oleo until tender. Add eggs and turkey broth. Mix and bake at 375° until brown.

title: mexican rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Mix ground beef and other ingredients together in casserole dish.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and casserole bubbles.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese until creamy.
Add eggs (one at a time). Blend well, add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour over crumb crust.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, cool 5 minutes.

title: spicy popcorn
directions: Combine all but popcorn.
Sprinkle on popcorn and toss lightly.
Serve immediately.

title: crunch sugar balls
directions: Melt over hot water the semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Remove from heat.
Add corn syrup and orange juice.
Combine vanilla wafer crumbs, powdered sugar and nuts.
Add to chocolate mixture and mix well.
Let stand about 30 minutes.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated or powdered sugar.
Allow to ripen in cool place in covered container.

title: fig (or date) bread pudding
directions: Add bread crumbs
to
hot
milk
and set aside to cool. When cool, add
all
other
ingredients	and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut in fat until it is like corn meal.
Combine the beaten eggs and milk.
Add to the flour mixture to make a very soft dough.
Turn on floured board and toss lightly.
Pat or roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutter for individual servings or cut in two sections and bake in sheets.
Spread one serving or sheet with butter and top with the other one.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.
When done, separate the two sections and serve sweetened strawberries between the layers and over the top.
Serve with cream, plain or whipped.

title: chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Using double boiler, melt the chips and almond together; when melted, add peanuts and drop from teaspoon onto waxed platter or cookie sheet.
Outstanding!

title: apples transparent
directions: Bring to a boil in deep pan to avoid boiling over.
Drop small whole apples (or larger halves) into mixture. Cook slowly.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter and blend all ingredients.
Add brown sugar until sweet enough.
Simmer until sauce thickens.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon.
Saute onion and brown meat.
Add brown sugar, mustard, catsup and vinegar.
Stir with beans and meat into dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain squash; add crackers, eggs, cheese, soup and pepper. Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy avocado salad
directions: Peel avocados and cut into bite size pieces.
Slice green onions into 1/2-inch lengths and tomato into 1/2-inch pieces. Combine all ingredients and toss lightly.

title: chocolate buttermilk sheet cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and resift with sugar, salt and cinnamon. Bring to a boil the margarine, water and cocoa; pour over the flour mixture.
Mix eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla together. Add to flour mixture.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple pepper salad
directions: Beat eggs in upper part of double boiler.
Add sugar, flour and salt, blended together.
Stir well, then add juices, water and vinegar.
Place over heat and stir until thick and creamy.
Chill and when ready to serve, add whipped cream.

title: easy chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken pieces in oil.
Add chopped garlic, onions and peppers.
Cook until half done.
Add spaghetti sauce, sweet basil, oregano, salt and pepper to taste and 1/2 cup red wine.
Simmer about 1 hour.

title: summer fruit salad
directions: Layer fruit in a large bowl in order given.
Spoon orange juice concentrate on top.
Cover and chill for 6 to 8 hours. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Spread nuts and coconut over bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Melt cream cheese and oleo in microwave.
Add powdered sugar to cream cheese and oleo.
Pour over cake batter and spread as evenly as possible.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: deep rapture slush
directions: Pour juices into blender container.
Add ice cubes, one at a time, while juice is blending.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Makes 2 (10 ounce) glasses.

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: Cut stems off spinach; wash leaves well.
Drain in colander. Chop spinach.
Cook bacon until browned and crisp; remove.
Drain on paper towels and crumble.
Add bacon, minced onion, salt and pepper to spinach.
Add vinegar to bacon fat; bring to a boil. Stir and pour over the spinach.
Serve immediately while spinach is still crisp. Yield: 4 servings.

title: chocolate pecan bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry).
Press firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: delicious beef and noodle
directions: Brown ground chuck and sprinkle with onion salt and garlic powder to taste.
Add mushroom soup, milk, and water.
Stir in Kitchen Bouquet.
Simmer about 2 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Mix together and drop by 1/2 teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mom's cream cheese salad
directions: Add cream cheese to water in saucepan and let come to boil, dissolving cheese.
Pour over orange jello, stir until dissolved. Add pineapple and nuts.
Add 3/4 to 1 cup water.
Stir well and refrigerate.

title: molske
directions: Add rennet to warm milk.
Let set until thick.
Cut in squares (do not remove from saucepan).
Boil slowly for 3 to 4 hours. (Color will be light brown when done.)
Stir frequently while simmering.
Serve in bowl with fruit sauce and cream.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Combine
soup,
milk and mayonnaise.
Pour over cabbage and margarine.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Stir 2 or 3 times. Sprinkle
cheese and cornflakes on top.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sour cream and add the other ingredients. Let sit overnight.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Place all ingredients into a large saucepan.
Mix thoroughly. Bring mixture to a boil.
Boil about 3 minutes.
Cool.
This may be stored in the refrigerator for several days.

title: dilled new potatoes and cheese
directions: Cook potatoes in 2-quart saucepan in lightly salted boiling water 10 to 15 minutes or until tender. Add peas.
Cook 1 minute. Drain well. Combine gravy, sour cream and dill.
Stir into vegetable mixture. Heat, do not boil, stirring occasionally. Makes 8 servings, about 4 cups.
Nutrients per serving (1/2 cup): 126 calories, 1 gram fat, 6 mg cholesterol and 332 sodium.

title: tomato soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Add tomatoes, onion, salt and sugar. Cover, reduce heat to medium-low and cook for 30 minutes.
Puree soup in batches in a blender or food processor.
Return soup to pot; simmer for 2 minutes.
Stir in basil just before serving.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine ingredients and cook on low heat until cheese is melted.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: In bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole, pour pineapple with juice, blueberries and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add dry cake mix, pour melted butter over mixture, top with pecans and add remaining sugar. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; pick off bone.
Melt margarine; stir into stuffing mix.
Layer in baking dish:
One layer of stuffing, layer of chicken, cream of celery soup (diluted with 1/4 cup water), layer of stuffing, layer of chicken and cream of chicken soup (diluted with 1/4 cup water).
Top with stuffing.
Brown in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: homemade chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut chicken into nugget size pieces. Melt margarine.
Combine in bowl and mix thoroughly, crumbs, Parmesan cheese, Accent, basil and thyme.
Dip chicken in margarine, then roll in crumb mixture.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet and bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill.
I like to add carrots and eggs.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in double boiler with milk.
When smooth, add pecans.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Let stand in freezer for 1 hour at least.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground round; add next 8 ingredients and simmer about 1 hour.
Combine cottage cheese with next 5 ingredients and set aside.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and rinse in cold water.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and layer noodles, 1/2 cottage cheese mixture, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas special fruitcake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine nuts, dates and cherries.
In another bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; add to nut mixture, stirring until nuts and fruits are well coated.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in vanilla, fold into nut mixture. Mix well. Pour into a greased and wax paper lined 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan before removing to a wire rack.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients with 3 cups of water in a large pot.
Boil until soft.
Add other ingredients and simmer until thickened.
Freeze in quart or pint jars.
Makes about 4 quarts.
Can be used with cooked ribs, as chicken baste or in crock-pot with beef or game meat.
Mix with meat and scoop onto buns.

title: robert's enchiladas
directions: Heat sauce adding first 6 ingredients.
Let simmer while preparing rest of dish.
Brown hamburger, adding same amounts of garlic, onion salt and cumin.
Stack on plate in following order: Fritos, hamburger, onions, cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and cheese. Serve with tomato sauce over top.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Set aside.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
When these mixtures have cooled, mix together and add eggs.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Dough may require hand mixing.
Put into greased mixing bowl.
Spread a thin coat of oil on dough and cover bowl loosely with damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator for at least 3 hours before using.
Remove part of dough.
Place on floured surface and roll out.
Cut in 3-inch circles.
Brush circles with warm melted butter and place on cookie sheet or in greased muffin tins to rise (approximately 3 hours).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Rolls can be prepared night before.
Remove from refrigerator to rise at least 4 hours before baking.

title: mounds cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions; add 1 stick margarine. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until done.
Melt the marshmallows, sugar and canned milk over low heat.
After melted, add the coconut.
Spread over cake.
Melt the chocolate chips and 1 stick margarine.
Spread over coconut mixture.
When cool, refrigerate to set chocolate.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients together.
Cut in butter and add raisins.
Add beaten egg with pumpkin and milk.
Add to mixture and mix only to combine ingredients.
Fill greased muffin pans 1/2 full and sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon sugar over each muffin.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dago cabbage
directions: Brown sausage in Dutch oven.
Do not drain.
Cut up cabbage over sausage; cut up the tomatoes over cabbage.
Add tomato sauce. Cover and let simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: scalloped apple sweet potatoes
directions: In a greased baking dish, layer half the sweet potatoes, apple slices and sprinkle with bread crumbs. Repeat layers. Pour syrup over top, sprinkle with salt. Squeeze margarine over the top, sprinkle with nuts. Generously sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Cover and bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until completely tender.
Drain. Dot 2-quart casserole dish with oleo.
Add part of macaroni and then part of cheese in alternate layers.
Cover with cheese.
Beat eggs and add the milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Add this to macaroni and cheese dish.
Bake until thickens in 400° oven.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Cut fish into 4 serving pieces if necessary.
Roll cornflakes into fine crumbs between layers of waxed paper.
Add salt and pepper to crumbs.
Pour milk into shallow pan.
Dip fish into milk, then into crumbs.
Arrange fish on baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray.
Sprinkle oil over fish.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: mexican stroganoff
directions: Note:
You can add 1/4 cup green chili salsa for zip.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Slice cookies thin, 1/4-inch. Cover baking dish with 1/2 the cookies.
Mix together cream cheese, egg, sugar, vanilla and sour cream.
Spread cream cheese filling over top of cookies.
Then put another layer of cookies over cream cheese filling.
Bake in 325° oven for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool and then refrigerate.
May sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Cut into bars.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble baked and cooled cornbread in large bowl.
Chop green onions, radishes, green pepper and tomatoes.
Add cornbread. Combine mayonnaise, cucumber dressing and mustard.
Add salt and white pepper, if desired.
Cheese cubes or boiled egg chunks may be added also.

title: linguine with garlic and lemon
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan; add garlic and next 3 ingredients, including mushrooms.
Add sauce to linguine and toss gently.
Serve immediately.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Cook a pork roast until tender.
Cut into little pieces.
Put in a large pot.

title: super shrimp spread(low-fat, no sugar)
directions: Chop shrimp in blender until fine.
Microwave cheese and butter until they blend smoothly.
Add shrimp, garlic and onion and whisk until well blended.
Pour mixture into a shallow dish and chill it.
Serve at room temperature on fat free crackers or fresh veggies.

title: lemonade
directions: Squeeze juice of lemons into a container and add sugar and water (to fill gallon).
Stir well.
Sliced lemon may be stirred in also.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Mix together the first five ingredients; let it rise until double in size.
Add salt and shortening; mix together and add enough
white flour to make a soft dough (not sticky or too stiff).
Let rise until double in bulk.
Put in two loaf pans; let rise until almost double.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to one hour.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix together salad dressing, sugar, cream cheese, pineapple, cherries and marshmallows.
Fold in the whipped cream.
A little cherry juice may be added, if desired.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, onions, celery and mayonnaise. Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle crackers on top.
Pour butter over crackers.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sunflower potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in 1-inch cubes and place in a baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with cheese and sprinkle nuts and seeds on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles, about 10 minutes.
Broil for 2 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: japanese honey cake(kasutera)
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Beat together eggs, sugar and honey until very thick.
Add flour, beating well.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan and bake 45 minutes.
But, stir the cake with
a
spoon
after the first 15 minutes of baking time. Continue
baking
in
ordinary
manner
next half hour. Allow cake
to
cool
in	pan.
Dust
cake with confectioners sugar, cut into strips and serve.

title: broccoli-cauliflower quickie(microwave)
directions: Layer vegetables.
Mix soup and Cheez Whiz and pour over top of vegetables.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave for 12 to 18 minutes on High.
Add onion rings and cook 1 to 2 additional minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quiche
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Mix milk, Bisquick and eggs. Sprinkle with onion, bacon and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, cherry Kool-Aid and sugar in pitcher. Chill until ready to serve.

title: chicken dish
directions: Layer chicken cut in bite size and partially cooked vegetables in long greased dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and rice and put on top of chicken mixture.
Add buttered crumbs on top and bake at 350° until brown and heated through.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Prepare raisins; simmer for 1/2 hour, covered with water, then use this in recipe.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well. Roll into small balls. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. May be frozen. When ready to serve, thaw about 45 minutes and reheat.

title: mock pink champagne
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar dissolves; cool.
Stir in cranberry, pineapple and orange juices.
Chill.
Just before serving, add carbonated beverage.
Yields 14 servings.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Saute beef and onion.
Mix Ricotta and Parmesan cheese with salt and pepper.
Spread over beef mixture.
Spread noodles on top.
Mix tomatoes, sauce and spices.
Pour over noodles. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beef (hamburger) stroganoff
directions: Brown onion and meat; drain fat when done.
Add soup; heat. Add sour cream and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook Minute rice. Spoon stroganoff over rice.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook sugar and milk until it forms a very soft ball.
Add dates and stir well.
Cook until this forms a firm soft ball.
Add nuts and beat until thick enough to spread on a wet towel; work into a long log.
Leave a few minutes and then wrap well in wax paper until ready to eat.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Combine dry gelatin, nuts and coconut.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Chill 1 hour or longer.
Shape into strawberries and roll in red sugar.
Tint sliced almonds with green food coloring in small bottle, shake well dry almonds on wax paper. Insert one sliced almond in top of berries to form leaves.
These make accents on cookie trays.

title: the blvd's throop's ambrosia
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Add milk gradually, stirring until smooth.
Cook, stirring until thickened. Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Then put quickly into remaining mixture in saucepan and cook 2 minutes over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake until meringue is brown.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: the cake that jack baked(dump cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Empty crushed pineapple and peach pie filling into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan; stir until mixed.
Cover mixture with dry yellow cake mix.
Slice butter and place on cake mix in rows until covered.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Grease a large pan.
Combine sugar, syrup, sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Cook over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cook until a soft ball forms when tested in cold water.
Add vanilla. Beat with beater until mixture holds its shape.
Add fruits and nuts. Pour into pan and cool.
Slice into small squares.

title: lemon champagne punch
directions: Mix lemonade, pineapple juice and Rhine wine in punch bowl. Add ice mold.
Add champagne and strawberries just before serving. Be careful, this one sneaks up on you.
Yields 50 punch cups.

title: meat loaf(for those who don't like dry meat loaf)
directions: In medium bowl, mix milk, eggs and all spices (not tomato sauce).
Add bite size bread chunks and let soak.
In a large bowl, mix meat and vegetables; add milk, bread and spice mixture. Blend well (hands work best).
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; hand form into 2 low meat loaves.
Press 4 fingers in a line into meat loaf to make 3 channels in the top of each loaf.
Cover top of loaves with cracker crumbs, then tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10; can be cut in half.
Can be doubled for a crowd.
Very moist if directions followed. Wonderful!

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients together and heat until cheese melts.
Serve over chips or use as dip.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Cut each unpeeled potato lengthwise into 4 wedges.
Place wedges peel side down in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine oil, Parmesan cheese, salt, garlic powder and paprika in a small bowl; mix well.
Brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, basting every 15 minutes with cheese mixture.
Turn potatoes. Bake for 15 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: monkey bread
directions: Separate biscuits; cut each one into 4 parts.
Put into a plastic bag:
white sugar and cinnamon.
Add the cut up biscuits and shake well.
Put into a Bundt pan that has been greased well. Arrange biscuits in pan.
Melt in saucepan oleo and brown sugar. Cook in saucepan until it comes to a boil; pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; leave 1 minute in pan when removing from oven.
Turn over on plate.
Tear off pieces; do not cut.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Add sugar, egg yolks and dates.
Stir constantly over low heat until all are mixed.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Set off heat.
Add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies. Cool.
Roll into balls and roll in coconut.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In water or broth, cook together onions, green pepper, celery and garlic until tender.
Set aside.
Boil chicken in water with salt and pepper added.
Remove chicken from broth.
Add spaghetti to broth and when cooked add soups, chicken, cooked vegetables and grated cheese.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: bark
directions: Butter 11 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Cover with one sleeve of saltine crackers.
Put brown sugar and butter in a pot and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour over saltines. Bake in 350° oven for 7 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over mixture and spread evenly.
Put in freezer or refrigerator.
When hard, turn on wax paper and break with wooden spoon.
Watch that it doesn't burn, 7 minutes may be too long.

title: cooked mayonnaise
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook over low temperature until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Good on potato salad.

title: lime salad
directions: In top of double boiler over boiling water on medium heat melt marshmallows in milk.
Add gelatin, stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese until smooth.
Remove from heat and add undrained pineapple and refrigerate until thickened.
Fold in whipped cream, mayonnaise and sugar.
Pour into large (9 x 13-inch) Pyrex dish or 2 medium molds.
Refrigerate.
Especially good with turkey and dressing.

title: seasoned marinated tomatoes
directions: Slice 3 large tomatoes and arrange on a platter.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Mix until blended.
Spoon over tomato slices and chill one hour.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat until creamy the sugar and oil.
Add soda, salt, carrots, vanilla and eggs.
Then add cinnamon and flour.
Place in a greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions, but add vegetables with seasoning package. Combine soup, milk and parsley; set aside.
In a 2 or 3-quart shallow baking dish, arrange stuffing across center of dish. Spoon thin layer of the soup mixture in casserole on each side of stuffing.
Arrange chicken over soup mixture; overlap if necessary.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil; bake for 15 minutes.
Uncover; bake 10 minutes more, until chicken is fork-tender.
Stir sauce before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon loaf with shrimp sauce
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid, flake salmon in bowl.
Add onion, parsley, lemon juice, salt, pepper, thyme and cracker crumbs.
Mix lightly.
Add enough milk to reserved liquid to make 1 cup.
Add liquid, eggs and butter to salmon; mix lightly.
Spoon into greased 8 1/4 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch glass loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour or until loaf is set in center.
Remove from pan onto platter.
Combine soup and 1/4 cup milk in saucepan; heat well. Serve with loaf.

title: greek roast chicken
directions: Rub the chicken inside and out with the cut surface of the lemon.
Rub outside with two tablespoons softened butter.
Place on rack in a roasting dish and bake in a 375° oven for 1/2 hour per pound.
Remove chicken and keep warm.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Make cake mix according to package directions.
Put in cupcake tins.
Mix the first 3 ingredients; fold in chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoons into unbaked cupcakes.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool and frost.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine these ingredients.
Press into cookie sheet (do not bake).

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey soup continental
directions: On top of stove, melt butter over low heat.
Add turkey and onion, cook until onion is well blended and slightly thick.
Add the potatoes, celery and broth.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add corn, milk and seasonings.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Season to taste with additional salt and pepper. Serve hot.
Garnish with parsley and serve with crackers, hard rolls, or toast.
Serves 8.
Use a large pan.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a 3 or 4-quart saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat; let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, spice and salt; add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Chill.
Form into 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar and place on a greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake in a moderately hot 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: olga's cherry coke salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Add enough water to make 2 cups of liquid.
Heat and dissolve jello. Then add rest of the ingredients.
Pour into mold or a pretty clear glass bowl. Chill until set.
Good at Christmas with a little whipped cream!

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Put all ingredients except sugar in blender and chop fine. Put in heavy saucepan. Add sugar and boil 5 minutes. Add 1 bottle Certo and small amount of green food coloring.
Boil 2 minutes and put in sterile jars.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and chop potatoes.
Place in a large pan; add onion and salt.
Cover with water.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Mix flour and milk until smooth.
Add to soup; salt and pepper it. Cook until slightly thickened.
Serve piping hot.

title: raspberry jello dessert
directions: Drain raspberries and save syrup.
Dissolve Jell-O in water. Add ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until partly set.
Then fold in raspberries and nuts.

title: easy cheesy asparagus bake
directions: Drain asparagus reserving a few pieces for garnish.
Place remaining asparagus in shallow 1 quart baking dish with red pepper.
Combine mayonnaise with cheese and green onions.
Fold in egg white.
Spread over asparagus.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 small servings.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix in mixing bowl the sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Pour into a saucepan and bring to boil the margarine, cocoa and water. Remove from heat; add sugar and flour mixture.
Mix well. Add vanilla, eggs, buttermilk and soda. Pour into well greased 11 x 16-inch pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
The cake is to be iced while hot, so begin mixing icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: no cook fruitcake
directions: Bake cake mix.
Cool; crumble into large bowl.
Add fruit to crumbs.
Mix all ingredients well.
Make the frosting mix.
Mix with cake and fruit.
Pack tightly into foil-lined pan.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches and 3/4 cup sugar.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine in a dish. Mix rest of sugar with flour, milk, baking powder and salt to make batter.
Pour batter over margarine.
Place peaches over batter.

title: barbara's candy
directions: Melt almond bark; crush Bugles.
Mix nuts and Bugles with almond bark.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: dill sweet pickles
directions: Drain brine from pickles.
Slice pickles and place back in jar.
Add sugar, cover and shake well.
Let stand in refrigerator for a few days, shaking occasionally.
Ready to eat after a few days.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix all together and spread over the dough.
Arrange the following fruit:

title: beef and vegetable bake
directions: Mix cooked hamburger, vegetables, dried onion soup and cream of mushroom soup together in bowl.
Add milk or water, if needed. Pour into baking dish.
Place Potato Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: braised root vegetables(carrots, celery, parsnips or turnips)
directions: Prepare vegetables by peeling and cutting into inch cubes or strips.
Brown lightly in the margarine in a heavy saucepan.
Add onion and celery; cook for 2 minutes, then add water.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove cover and allow liquid to evaporate.
Serves 4.

title: nantucket cranberry pie
directions: Layer in buttered 10-inch pie pan the cranberries, chopped nuts and 1/2 cup sugar. Mix melted oleo, flour, 1 cup sugar, flavoring and eggs. Pour over the first mixture. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix in order until well blended.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool and then frost.

title: jello cake
directions: Make cake according to package.
Dissolve Jell-O without boiling water.
Allow to cool, but not to harden.
Make holes in cake and pour Jell-O in holes.
Put in refrigerator to chill. Frost with Dream Whip and top with nuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice.
Set aside.
Saute onions in butter about 5 minutes.
Empty soup in 1-quart casserole.
Add broccoli and rice.
Then add onions and Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir ingredients about halfway through baking time.

title: lazy stroganoff(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Mix all together and bake covered at 275° for 3 to 4 hours. Serve over cooked rice or noodles.
Great for a busy day.

title: marshmallow creme fudge
directions: Bring ingredients to a full boil, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 12 ounces chocolate chips and stir until well mixed.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.

title: glass cleaner
directions: To easily measure honey, molasses or syrup, dip spoon or cup in oil or hot water before measuring.

title: faye's chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Pour evenly into 2 pie crusts.
Cover with other 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken yakisoba(makes 4 servings)
directions: Use large bowls, this makes very generous servings!

title: super bowl cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees, for glass dish 375 degrees. Combine crumbs, cocoa, sugar and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9 in. baking dish or pan.
Pour eagle brand milk evenly over crust.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients. Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes for until browned.
Cool, or chill thoroughly if desired cut into bars.
Store loosely at room temperature.

title: quaker oat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°F.
Line 12 muffin cups with paper baking cups.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix beef and onion; add Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and milk to egg.
Mix and add to bread crumbs.
Add parsley.
Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into small round balls.

title: taco chip dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain, set aside.
Melt in pan, cheese and margarine.
Add salsa and ground beef.
Pour over chips or use as a dip.

title: corn dogs
directions: Pat frankfurters dry with paper towel.
Heat oil 2 to 3 minutes to 365°.
Mix flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add shortening. Dissolve yeast in water; add to buttermilk until moist.
Cover and chill.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: krazy krunch
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave according to instructions on the package. Add peanuts and cereal to melted almond bark.
Mix until all of the peanuts and cereal are covered with the melted almond bark.
Lay out the sheets of waxed paper and spoon the mixture out onto the wax paper to harden.

title: swiss steak and rice
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip steaks in flour.
Heat shortening and brown steaks about 15 minutes.
Pour V-8 juice over the top.
Add onion, then the pepper.
Heat to boiling; simmer 45 minutes, until tender.
When done, remove meat.
Add rice in juice.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add marshmallows and warm mixture a little on stove.
When cool, add pineapple and refrigerate until partially congealed.
Fold in cottage cheese, nuts and cherries; then add whipped cream.
Refrigerate.
Will keep up to 4 days.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn and flour with a wire whisk.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake in a buttered dish for one hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: root beer shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and mix at high speed until foamy.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Grease a Bundt pan and place pecans in bottom.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Quarter biscuits. Roll in sugar/cinnamon mixture and place in pan.
You will probably have about 3 layers. Melt margarine. Add brown sugar to margarine and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda.
Add water and vinegar; mix well. Batter fish and fry.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Increase heat; cover and boil until cranberries pop, stirring occasionally, about 8 minutes. Transfer mixture to bowl; stir in pecans.
Cover and refrigerate until cold (mixture will thicken as it cools).
Can be made 4 days ahead.
Keep chilled.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Using a food processor,
mince
onion.
Cook
onion and garlic in heavy saucepan.
Add butter and olive oil until just beginning to brown.
Separate mushroom stems from caps.
Mince stems and 1 cup mushroom caps in food processor.
Add to onion mixture.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well
with	buttermilk,
leaving
thick.
Dip
with teaspoon and cook at
300° to 350° (with enough cooking oil to float) until golden brown.	Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: spinach and cheese dip
directions: Place spinach in a 1-quart microwavable casserole dish and microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes, until defrosted and cooked. Let cool slightly and then place clean dry towel in dish to remove excess water.
In a 2-quart bowl, combine spinach, cream cheese, tomato, onions, garlic and jalapenos.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, until mixture is smooth.
Stir in cheese and milk. Season with salt and pepper.
Serve piping hot with tortilla chips.

title: ice cream snowballs
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan a day ahead.
Crumble day old cake finely.
Drop 1 scoop of ice cream into crumbs.
Pack crumbs around ice cream like a snowball. Freeze.
